01:02.595 --> 01:04.028
With my personal trainer,

01:04.096 --> 01:05.530
from Tampa Bay, Florida,

01:05.598 --> 01:07.225
Tony Little,

01:07.300 --> 01:08.324
[Applause]

01:08.401 --> 01:09.891
Hey, Tony, welcome,

01:09.969 --> 01:12.904
Thank you for being here,

01:12.972 --> 01:15.406
Let me ask you a question,

01:15.475 --> 01:17.909
95% of people
gain their weight back,

01:17.977 --> 01:19.911
Is it ever going to end?

01:19.979 --> 01:21.412
We 're going to educate them,

01:21.481 --> 01:22.914
Let me show you something,

01:22.982 --> 01:24.415
what I call "fitness past,"

01:24.484 --> 01:26.076
What's all this?

01:26.152 --> 01:27.551
[Grrr]

01:27.620 --> 01:29.087
The original!

01:29.155 --> 01:32.591
Ha! I can't believe it.

01:32.659 --> 01:36.618
Ohh...thanks.

01:36.696 --> 01:38.561
This is a sign.

01:38.631 --> 01:39.962
He's always been king
of his world,

01:40.033 --> 01:41.466
We'll teach him fear,

01:41.534 --> 01:43.263
"We're millionaires, boys.

01:43.336 --> 01:46.271
I'll share it with all of you."

01:49.109 --> 01:51.543
He was a king and a god

01:51.611 --> 01:53.044
in the world he knew,

01:53.113 --> 01:55.047
But now he comes
to civilization,

01:55.115 --> 01:56.548
merely a captive,

01:56.616 --> 01:59.210
a show to gratify
your curiosity,

01:59.285 --> 02:00.650
" Ladies and gentlemen..."

02:00.720 --> 02:01.687
Look at...

02:01.754 --> 02:04.154
" Kong, the eighth wonder
of the world."

02:04.224 --> 02:05.885
[Fanfare]

02:05.959 --> 02:07.586
There he is.

02:07.660 --> 02:09.924
If only he could pitch.

02:09.996 --> 02:11.395
Good one now.

02:11.464 --> 02:12.897
Come on! Heads up!

02:12.966 --> 02:15.127
Put it in there.

02:16.202 --> 02:18.227
Strike!

02:20.440 --> 02:21.372
Hello, fellas.

02:21.441 --> 02:23.875
Well, well, the pride of the Yankees.

02:23.943 --> 02:26.377
They fly you down in their private jet?

02:26.446 --> 02:27.879
In fact, they offered. Yeah.

02:27.947 --> 02:30.381
I heard you were in big trouble.

02:30.450 --> 02:31.883
Where'd you hear that?

02:31.951 --> 02:33.384
The kid you found, McGowan?

02:33.453 --> 02:34.886
He's zero for 60?

02:34.954 --> 02:36.854
0 for 61.

02:36.923 --> 02:38.857
You didn't see last night's game.

02:38.925 --> 02:40.859
Who cares about last night's game?

02:40.927 --> 02:43.020
Let me tell you how it works.

02:43.096 --> 02:44.529
The world's a jungle.

02:44.597 --> 02:46.030
You walk into the jungle,

02:46.099 --> 02:48.363
come outwith Kong,
you're a hero.

02:48.434 --> 02:50.402
They forget about
last night's game.

02:50.470 --> 02:51.402
Who's Kong?

02:51.471 --> 02:52.529
Catcher, Iowa State.

02:52.605 --> 02:55.438
No, the animal!
In the movies.

02:55.508 --> 02:56.975
Forget it.

02:59.712 --> 03:00.701
Strike!

03:00.780 --> 03:02.839
Whew! The kid can pitch.

03:02.916 --> 03:04.349
He's gonna finish college, too.

03:04.417 --> 03:05.850
What's he now, junior?

03:05.919 --> 03:06.977
Freshman.

03:07.053 --> 03:07.985
Freshman?

03:08.054 --> 03:09.681
31 /2 years, can't touch him.

03:09.756 --> 03:11.690
Can't even talk to his parents.

03:11.758 --> 03:13.225
They're devout Catholics.

03:13.293 --> 03:15.386
Well, I learned one thing,

03:15.461 --> 03:17.395
no use salivating over a player

03:17.463 --> 03:19.556
you're never gonna get,
right, Phil?

03:19.632 --> 03:20.564
Right.

03:20.633 --> 03:22.066
If my bosses call,

03:22.135 --> 03:24.069
tell 'em I already showed up.

03:24.137 --> 03:26.071
By the way, I'm leaving now.

03:26.139 --> 03:28.073
You can make fun of me.

03:28.141 --> 03:29.699
Yeah, don't worry. We will.

03:36.983 --> 03:38.917
Tommy!

03:38.985 --> 03:40.418
How are you?

03:40.486 --> 03:41.418
Good.

03:41.487 --> 03:42.920
I'm Al Percolo...

03:42.989 --> 03:45.924
scout with the New York Yankees.

03:45.992 --> 03:47.425
Wow. The Yankees?

03:47.493 --> 03:49.927
I didn't know you guys were coming.

03:49.996 --> 03:51.429
Here we are.

03:51.497 --> 03:53.931
Listen, you're really good.

03:54.000 --> 03:55.024
Thanks.

03:55.101 --> 03:56.864
You're gonna finish
school though, huh?

03:56.936 --> 03:58.369
It's not my idea.

03:58.438 --> 03:59.871
I'd kill to play
for the Yankees,

03:59.939 --> 04:01.873
but that's what
my parents want.

04:01.941 --> 04:03.875
I thought you wanted to finish.

04:03.943 --> 04:05.877
No, but what am I gonna do?

04:05.945 --> 04:07.879
Let me talk to your parents.

04:07.947 --> 04:09.881
Want to come have dinner?

04:09.949 --> 04:11.382
Tonight? I wasn't really invited.

04:11.451 --> 04:12.884
I'm inviting you.

04:12.952 --> 04:14.886
I accept.

04:18.458 --> 04:20.892
Mmm. These carrots
are so sweet,

04:20.959 --> 04:22.894
you could eat them for dessert.

04:22.962 --> 04:24.156
Thank you.

04:28.468 --> 04:32.165
You know, the Yankees
are very geared to religion.

04:33.339 --> 04:35.432
I couldn't help noticing

04:35.508 --> 04:37.442
that beautiful painting
up there.

04:37.510 --> 04:40.775
That's virtually
the same exact picture

04:40.847 --> 04:42.747
that hangs in the clubhouse.

04:44.017 --> 04:46.451
Terrific likeness, isn't it?

04:48.688 --> 04:50.121
You've heard of Mickey Mantle?

04:50.189 --> 04:52.851
Did you know
his sister was a nun?

04:52.925 --> 04:54.859
I hadn't heard that.

04:54.927 --> 04:56.690
Yes, indeed, a very famous one.

04:56.763 --> 04:58.355
What was her name?

04:58.431 --> 05:01.889
Gee, I believe
it was also Micki,

05:01.968 --> 05:03.401
but with an "I."

05:03.469 --> 05:06.233
Sister Micki Elizabeth Mantle.

05:06.306 --> 05:07.739
Some nun.

05:08.808 --> 05:11.140
Tommy, you haven't
touched your food.

05:11.210 --> 05:12.643
I'm not hungry.

05:12.712 --> 05:15.010
It's no excuse.
Finish your food.

05:15.081 --> 05:17.413
He reminds me of me.

05:17.483 --> 05:21.419
Couldn't get me to finish my food
if you paid me.

05:21.487 --> 05:23.421
Now try to keep me away.

05:23.489 --> 05:24.751
May I say something?

05:24.824 --> 05:25.984
Yeah.

05:26.059 --> 05:27.993
I believe education
is most important

05:28.061 --> 05:29.995
and that people
should finish school.

05:30.063 --> 05:31.655
I know Tommy does, too.

05:31.731 --> 05:33.665
But Tommy has a dilemma,

05:33.733 --> 05:36.497
and that is that...
he's gifted.

05:36.569 --> 05:39.504
And he's really concerned.

05:39.572 --> 05:42.006
What does he do with that gift?

05:42.075 --> 05:46.011
Does he sign on the dotted line
right now, make $500,000,

05:46.079 --> 05:49.014
go to the biggest city
in the world,

05:49.082 --> 05:53.109
and become a member of the most
prestigious baseball team that ever was,

05:53.186 --> 05:55.120
or does he continue
his schooling,

05:55.188 --> 05:58.248
possibly trip over a book
on the way to math class

05:58.324 --> 05:59.723
and be worth nothing?

05:59.792 --> 06:04.388
But he knows that with the kind of money
you make in baseball,

06:04.464 --> 06:06.398
even if you didn't
finish school,

06:06.466 --> 06:08.525
your education
doesn't have to stop.

06:08.601 --> 06:12.401
Tommy knows that many
of the ballplayers hire tutors.

06:12.472 --> 06:14.406
Did you know that?

06:14.474 --> 06:16.908
Babe Ruth, Ty Cobb,
Lou Gehrig...

06:16.976 --> 06:20.537
they all had tutors
with them in the dugout.

06:20.613 --> 06:21.545
Lou Gehrig...

06:21.614 --> 06:22.979
had a tutor?

06:23.049 --> 06:24.482
Oh, yes, ma'am. Yeah.

06:24.550 --> 06:26.814
Didn't he also have
a terrible disease?

06:26.886 --> 06:30.287
He did, but he didn't
get it from the tutor.

06:30.356 --> 06:33.553
I think he got that in college.

06:33.626 --> 06:35.719
So you can see Tommy's dilemma.

06:35.795 --> 06:37.786
Do I take God's gift

06:37.864 --> 06:42.062
and go play for the greatest
baseball team that ever lived,

06:42.135 --> 06:46.572
or do I stay in a small school
and hope I don't trip?

06:46.639 --> 06:49.472
Is this what
you were thinking, Tommy?

06:49.542 --> 06:52.204
That's exactly...right.

06:52.278 --> 06:55.441
I can have a tutor, Mom,
right in the dugout.

06:55.515 --> 06:57.380
Please, Mom, let me play.

06:57.450 --> 06:58.382
Please?

06:58.451 --> 07:00.118
Please?

07:00.119 --> 07:00.175
Please?

07:00.253 --> 07:04.383
And in his major league
debut, Tommy Lacy,

07:04.457 --> 07:07.051
What a great afternoon
for Yankee baseball,

07:07.126 --> 07:09.560
I'm Bobby Mercer,
along with John Sturly,

07:09.629 --> 07:11.563
the radio voice of the Yankees,

07:11.631 --> 07:13.565
John has seen Tommy Lacy pitch,

07:13.633 --> 07:15.567
I sure have, a year ago,

07:15.635 --> 07:17.569
We gave up Reynolds for Lacy?

07:17.637 --> 07:20.071
Sure hope it's
the right thing to do.

07:20.139 --> 07:22.073
Wait till you see him pitch.

07:22.141 --> 07:24.575
You'd give up two Reynolds
to get him.

07:25.978 --> 07:29.414
By the way, how come he's not
with the team?

07:29.482 --> 07:31.109
I wouldn't worry about it.

07:31.184 --> 07:33.118
[Vomiting]

07:35.488 --> 07:36.420
[Toilet Flushes]

07:36.489 --> 07:38.354
You feeling better, Tommy?

07:38.424 --> 07:39.618
No.

07:39.692 --> 07:42.627
Come on, son.
You got to take the mound.

07:42.695 --> 07:43.627
It's game time.

07:43.696 --> 07:45.129
No, I can't.

07:45.198 --> 07:47.166
Tell them I can't.

07:47.233 --> 07:49.167
What do you mean you can't?

07:49.235 --> 07:51.169
There's 30,000 people
sitting out there

07:51.237 --> 07:53.364
just waiting to see you pitch.

07:53.439 --> 07:54.804
Tell them I can't.

07:54.874 --> 07:56.239
I can't do it.

07:56.309 --> 07:57.674
I ain't telling them nothing.

07:57.743 --> 07:59.370
You tell them.

07:59.445 --> 08:01.208
Aagg.

08:01.280 --> 08:02.212
What?

08:02.281 --> 08:03.714
Get him out of there.

08:03.783 --> 08:05.216
Well, crawl underneath.

08:05.284 --> 08:07.218
I don't care what you do.

08:07.286 --> 08:09.720
Just get him out of there.

08:09.789 --> 08:10.949
Al.

08:12.024 --> 08:13.048
Al!

08:13.125 --> 08:15.286
Your kid's locked himself
in the crapper.

08:15.361 --> 08:16.293
What?

08:16.362 --> 08:17.727
Lacy's locked in the crapper.

08:17.797 --> 08:19.196
He won't come out.

08:19.265 --> 08:22.257
Here we go,
The Yankees take the field,

08:22.335 --> 08:24.769
Kid, you're supposed
to be on the field!

08:24.837 --> 08:26.771
Listen, I made
a mistake, O.K.?

08:26.839 --> 08:28.272
O.K. I need the Lord.

08:28.341 --> 08:29.774
What's going on?

08:29.842 --> 08:31.275
I want the Lord.

08:31.344 --> 08:32.777
He don't want to play, Al.

08:32.845 --> 08:34.278
Let me talk to him.

08:34.347 --> 08:36.508
Tommy, Al Percolo.
How are ya?

08:36.582 --> 08:38.515
Mr. Percolo,
I made a mistake.

08:38.583 --> 08:40.017
I got to go home.

08:40.086 --> 08:41.986
You can't go home, Tommy.

08:42.054 --> 08:44.887
People are waiting.
Everyone wants to see you pitch.

08:44.957 --> 08:45.889
Come on.

08:45.958 --> 08:48.392
I can't pitch
for a crowd this size.

08:48.461 --> 08:50.122
I can't do it.

08:50.196 --> 08:53.131
You've pitched in front
of full stadiums at home.

08:53.199 --> 08:54.632
What's the difference?

08:54.700 --> 08:56.133
It wasn't Yankee Stadium.

08:56.202 --> 08:58.193
It's... I don't
want to be here.

08:58.271 --> 08:59.704
I'll give the money back.

08:59.772 --> 09:02.707
I don't want it back,
you son of a bitch.

09:02.775 --> 09:05.209
Sorry, Tommy.
I'm on the line here.

09:05.278 --> 09:08.213
I gave up a draft choice
to get you.

09:08.281 --> 09:12.217
Just compose yourself, get out there,
and play a good game.

09:12.285 --> 09:15.152
No, I can't do it.
I want the Lord.

09:15.221 --> 09:16.654
I need the Lord.

09:16.722 --> 09:18.155
Shh, shh, shh.

09:18.224 --> 09:20.158
Let me tell you something.
Listen.

09:20.226 --> 09:22.660
The Lord wants you
to play baseball.

09:22.728 --> 09:23.888
Yes, he does.

09:23.963 --> 09:26.056
He wants me to finish school.

09:26.132 --> 09:27.565
No, he doesn't.

09:27.633 --> 09:30.067
God's not interested
in people finishing school.

09:30.136 --> 09:32.570
He doesn't care about
the graduation ceremonies.

09:32.638 --> 09:34.572
That's why they're
in the afternoon.

09:34.640 --> 09:37.074
They'd be at night
if it was important.

09:37.143 --> 09:39.407
So, go out there and play ball.

09:39.478 --> 09:41.912
This is what
God wants you to do.

09:41.981 --> 09:44.415
I don't know much,
but I know this.

09:44.483 --> 09:45.780
God wants you to pitch.

09:45.851 --> 09:47.785
I think I made a mistake.

09:47.853 --> 09:49.787
God says people
can make mistakes.

09:49.855 --> 09:51.789
God never said
people make mistakes.

09:51.857 --> 09:53.791
Where did you hear that shit?

09:53.859 --> 09:55.258
God said nothing like that.

09:55.328 --> 09:57.421
He said honor thy father,
thy mother,

09:57.496 --> 09:58.827
and thy Yankee contract.

09:58.898 --> 09:59.956
I'm coming under.

10:00.032 --> 10:01.226
There's some delay.

10:01.300 --> 10:04.235
Apparently, Tommy Lacy is still
in the locker room.

10:04.303 --> 10:05.736
I know what he's doing.

10:05.805 --> 10:07.932
He's looking at himself
in the mirror

10:08.007 --> 10:10.942
in that Yankee uniform
and can't get over it.

10:11.010 --> 10:14.104
It's a stunning sight,
first time you put that on.

10:14.180 --> 10:15.545
Something seems to happen.

10:15.615 --> 10:16.547
Come on.

10:16.616 --> 10:18.049
No, no! Please!

10:18.117 --> 10:19.550
Now, listen to me.

10:19.619 --> 10:21.553
Use your change-up
sparingly, understand?

10:21.621 --> 10:23.555
You're going to be fine.

10:23.623 --> 10:24.817
No! Aah!

10:24.890 --> 10:28.656
[Organ Plays Charge]

10:36.802 --> 10:39.134
[Mexican Hat Dance Plays]

10:49.048 --> 10:50.208
What's the trouble?

10:50.282 --> 10:51.214
No trouble.

10:51.283 --> 10:52.716
He's out there, isn't he?

10:56.022 --> 10:58.582
Lacy's first warmup
pitch was very wild,

10:58.658 --> 11:00.091
way over Jackson’s head.

11:03.229 --> 11:05.663
[Woman]
Get it over the plate, dummy!

11:06.832 --> 11:08.766
Another wild pitch,

11:08.834 --> 11:10.233
Lacy cannot find his control.

11:10.302 --> 11:11.564
What is this?

11:11.637 --> 11:13.571
Is this a joke, these warmups?

11:13.639 --> 11:15.834
They're warmups.
That's what they're for.

11:15.908 --> 11:19.844
To see how far away
he can throw it from the men?

11:19.912 --> 11:21.243
You're getting closer.

11:21.313 --> 11:22.746
Looking for a pitching coach?

11:22.815 --> 11:24.715
Lacy has stopped his warmups.

11:24.784 --> 11:26.615
Now he's looking as if to...

11:26.686 --> 11:28.119
Oh, my goodness!

11:28.187 --> 11:30.121
Uh-oh. That's
a little embarrassing.

11:30.189 --> 11:33.625
Tommy must've eaten some
bad food before coming out

11:33.693 --> 11:36.457
because he has regurgitated
all over the mound.

11:36.529 --> 11:38.588
And here comes
the cleaning crew.

11:38.664 --> 11:41.098
Well, we've just seen
a baseball first.

11:41.167 --> 11:43.601
Tommy Lacy taking
himself out of the game.

11:43.669 --> 11:47.070
Listen, it happens to fighters,
it happens to runners.

11:47.139 --> 11:48.572
You eat that bad turkey,

11:48.641 --> 11:50.404
this is what happens to you.

11:50.476 --> 11:52.410
No, no, no.
Don't stop him.

11:52.478 --> 11:54.105
Just let him go.

11:55.381 --> 11:57.906
I don't care.
Just let him go.

11:57.983 --> 11:59.450
Just a case of butterflies.

11:59.518 --> 12:01.418
I've seen it a thousand times.

12:01.487 --> 12:02.715
He's gonna be fine.

12:02.788 --> 12:05.723
Right now, he's
running down the road

12:05.791 --> 12:08.225
with his clothes over his back.

12:08.294 --> 12:13.129
You wanna run after him
and tell him he's gonna be fine?

12:13.199 --> 12:14.632
He's running where?

12:14.700 --> 12:16.133
I don't know, Al.

12:16.202 --> 12:17.635
Somewhere towards the turnpike.

12:17.703 --> 12:21.070
I want to see you in my office
in five minutes.

12:21.140 --> 12:24.443
Tommy Lacy's very expensive,
very brief big league debut,

12:24.577 --> 12:29.708
Vapadelapa, Nochitos,
Escondrio...

12:29.782 --> 12:31.249
Playa Del Muerte.

12:32.485 --> 12:33.417
Huegos...

12:33.486 --> 12:35.511
I never heard of any
of these places.

12:35.588 --> 12:38.022
They're a little off
the beaten track, Al.

12:38.090 --> 12:41.890
You're the first scout we've ever sent
this deep into Mexico.

12:41.961 --> 12:43.656
But is there baseball there?

12:43.729 --> 12:45.162
Oh, I'm sure there is.

12:45.231 --> 12:47.665
Maybe not in the form
we know it,

12:47.733 --> 12:52.500
but I'm gonna expect a daily report
from each of these towns.

12:52.571 --> 12:56.007
Come on. You know I'm not
gonna find anybody there.

12:56.075 --> 12:57.440
It's a waste of time.

12:57.510 --> 12:59.137
Is this a grudge trip?

13:00.479 --> 13:02.413
Yes, it is, Al.

13:04.483 --> 13:08.283
Well, why don’t you
just fire me?

13:08.354 --> 13:09.912
I thought of that.

13:09.989 --> 13:11.889
I like this better.

13:11.957 --> 13:13.390
If you're trying to banish me,

13:13.459 --> 13:14.892
at least pick a place

13:14.960 --> 13:16.393
where somebody plays baseball.

13:16.462 --> 13:17.895
What about Alaska or Canada?

13:17.963 --> 13:21.399
If I had my choice,
it'd be a leper colony.

13:21.467 --> 13:23.799
I think it's illegal.
This will have to do.

13:25.171 --> 13:26.103
Adios.

13:27.206 --> 13:28.639
Hasta la vista,

13:28.707 --> 13:30.140
You be safe, Al.

