~ Gootchie, gootchie,
gootchie ~~

14:08.781 --> 14:09.873
No, no.

14:09.949 --> 14:11.883
No, no, no, no, no.

14:11.951 --> 14:13.111
It's a foot?
Is that a foot?

14:13.185 --> 14:15.517
Huh? No, no.

14:16.889 --> 14:19.323
Where I come from
that's a felony.

14:19.391 --> 14:20.824
No, thank you.

14:23.562 --> 14:25.894
[Speaking Spanish]

14:25.965 --> 14:27.364
Where are the umpires?

14:27.433 --> 14:28.866
Any umpires out there?

14:28.934 --> 14:31.368
You just want to
share that, don’t you?

14:31.437 --> 14:34.031
You finish it.
I'll use the napkin.

14:34.106 --> 14:37.075
Senor Ramirez, telefono,
Senor Ramirez,

14:38.844 --> 14:41.176
Where's the pitcher going?

14:41.247 --> 14:42.612
Telephone call.

14:42.681 --> 14:43.909
Telephone call?

14:43.983 --> 14:46.417
How do you like that?

14:55.160 --> 14:57.355
No, no, no, no.

14:58.597 --> 14:59.529
No.

15:13.312 --> 15:14.643
Safe!

15:17.950 --> 15:18.882
It's pouring.

15:18.951 --> 15:20.248
They're not gonna stop?

15:20.319 --> 15:23.311
Too much rain-o.

15:23.389 --> 15:25.880
You know, the rain's
pouring...down.

15:25.958 --> 15:27.323
They should stop.

15:27.393 --> 15:30.590
No stop. Stop-po rain.

15:30.663 --> 15:31.652
Uh, alto,

15:31.730 --> 15:34.858
Alto 'cause of the rain.

15:34.934 --> 15:38.529
No, senor, they wait
for the rain.

15:38.604 --> 15:41.334
Better slide.

15:56.188 --> 15:58.349
[Coughing]

16:01.927 --> 16:03.861
[Horn Honks]

16:03.929 --> 16:06.420
Whoa!

16:06.498 --> 16:07.965
[Beep]

16:08.033 --> 16:10.627
No!

16:10.703 --> 16:12.637
Whoaa!

16:33.459 --> 16:35.393
What is this, a kennel?

16:43.469 --> 16:45.096
How are ya?

16:46.805 --> 16:49.899
My God, this is really a dump.

16:49.975 --> 16:51.465
Here.

16:55.147 --> 16:58.344
[Electronic Translator]
Quiero un habitacion con bano?

16:58.417 --> 17:01.580
I speak enough where
we don't have to do that.

17:01.653 --> 17:02.585
You're kidding?

17:02.654 --> 17:05.088
You know, I didn't mean dump

17:05.156 --> 17:06.886
in the traditional sense.

17:06.959 --> 17:07.983
Name?

17:08.060 --> 17:09.993
Percolo. I have
a reservation.

17:10.061 --> 17:12.553
P-E-R-C-O-L-O.

17:12.631 --> 17:13.858
Si, Percolo.

17:13.932 --> 17:15.229
You got a credit card?

17:15.300 --> 17:16.232
Oh, yeah.

17:18.936 --> 17:21.371
What brings you here?
Are you visiting?

17:21.440 --> 17:25.376
No, no, no. I'm here
to see a baseball game.

17:25.444 --> 17:26.911
I'm a scout.

17:26.979 --> 17:30.915
Oh, you must be here
to see Steve Nebraska.

17:30.983 --> 17:32.883
Who?

17:32.951 --> 17:34.179
Steve Nebraska.

17:34.253 --> 17:35.618
That's not why you’re here?

17:35.687 --> 17:37.621
I don't know who that is.

17:37.689 --> 17:39.179
You don't know who that is?

17:39.258 --> 17:41.692
That's the greatest ballplayer
that ever lived.

17:41.760 --> 17:43.091
That's who he is.

17:43.162 --> 17:45.096
And this is the Four Seasons.

17:45.164 --> 17:46.597
You're in for a treat.

17:46.665 --> 17:48.895
Really?
Well, I hope so.

17:48.967 --> 17:52.494
You got a porter that could
help me with the bags?

17:52.571 --> 17:54.732
No. You want the job?

17:56.408 --> 17:58.273
Ron, I can barely hear you.

17:58.343 --> 18:01.278
I don't even know
if you can hear me.

18:01.346 --> 18:03.940
As usual, I have
nothing new to report.

18:04.016 --> 18:05.449
Uh, hold on, Al.

18:05.517 --> 18:07.451
I want more details than that.

18:07.519 --> 18:08.850
More details?

18:08.921 --> 18:10.616
All right.

18:10.689 --> 18:13.123
Yesterday I saw a game played

18:13.192 --> 18:16.127
by five men,
two women, a child,

18:16.195 --> 18:18.493
and a goat at third base.

18:18.564 --> 18:21.761
Really?
Was the goat any good?

18:21.834 --> 18:23.267
Very funny, Ron.

18:23.335 --> 18:26.168
I got to go.
I got a game to see.

18:26.238 --> 18:27.671
Enjoy the game.

18:27.739 --> 18:30.139
Uh, my regards to the goat.

18:30.275 --> 18:32.368
[Band Plays]

19:22.995 --> 19:25.930
[Gong Sounds]

19:25.998 --> 19:30.367
[Band Plays
The Star-Spangled Banner]

19:55.027 --> 19:58.929
[Band Forgets Music]

20:29.561 --> 20:32.155
Play ball!

20:39.705 --> 20:43.402
[Band Plays Charge]

20:43.475 --> 20:46.239
- Nebraska!
- Nebraska!

20:52.517 --> 20:53.609
Strike!

20:59.224 --> 21:00.555
Strike!

21:04.129 --> 21:05.221
Strike 3!

21:05.297 --> 21:06.730
This is unreal!

21:15.107 --> 21:17.166
Jesus!

21:22.214 --> 21:23.647
Strike 3!

21:30.989 --> 21:32.422
Nebraska! Nebraska!

21:32.491 --> 21:33.924
Nebraska! Nebraska!

21:33.992 --> 21:35.789
Nebraska! Nebraska!

21:35.861 --> 21:38.989
Don't tell me he can hit, too.

22:07.959 --> 22:09.221
I found him.

22:09.294 --> 22:11.057
I found him! I found him!

22:11.129 --> 22:13.893
I found Kong! I found Kong!

22:13.965 --> 22:18.670
Oh, my God Almighty!

22:18.804 --> 22:21.864
[Singing In Spanish]

22:49.334 --> 22:51.768
They just don't leave you
alone around here.

22:51.837 --> 22:53.065
They love you.

22:53.138 --> 22:54.571
Mmm, I love this salad.

22:54.639 --> 22:56.072
Do you like it?

22:56.141 --> 22:57.005
Yeah.

22:57.075 --> 22:58.007
Want one?

22:58.076 --> 23:00.044
No. I ate at the game.

23:00.112 --> 23:01.409
Rat dog, huh?

23:03.281 --> 23:04.373
What?

23:04.449 --> 23:05.381
[Laughing]

23:05.450 --> 23:06.883
That's a joke, right?

23:06.952 --> 23:08.385
I'm just kidding.

23:08.453 --> 23:09.886
They got good stuff there.

23:12.891 --> 23:15.325
I'm sorry.
I can't believe it.

23:15.394 --> 23:16.827
You're from the Yankees?

23:16.895 --> 23:18.362
That is so cool.

23:18.430 --> 23:20.921
Well, they're certainly
a legendary team.

23:20.999 --> 23:24.435
Yeah. Yeah. I couldn't imagine
playing for the Yankees.

23:24.503 --> 23:26.334
I mean, that's just too much.

23:26.405 --> 23:28.839
The Yankees would be
lucky to have you.

23:28.907 --> 23:30.636
Are you kidding?

23:30.709 --> 23:31.903
I don't know.

23:31.977 --> 23:34.912
I don't think the competition
down here's so great.

23:34.980 --> 23:36.413
Maybe I'm just playing good

23:36.481 --> 23:38.415
because I'm not playing
against anybody.

23:38.483 --> 23:39.916
You don't have any competition.

23:39.985 --> 23:43.921
I have never seen anybody pitch
like that in my whole life.

23:43.989 --> 23:45.422
You ever had it clocked?

23:45.490 --> 23:47.890
Gotta be over 100 miles
an hour.

23:47.959 --> 23:48.948
Think so?

23:49.027 --> 23:51.928
And where did you learn
to hit like that?

23:51.997 --> 23:55.558
I just get the bat off
my shoulder and...

23:55.634 --> 24:00.662
God, I am so lucky no other scouts
have ever seen you play.

24:00.739 --> 24:03.674
A while ago, this guy
from Chicago came down,

24:03.742 --> 24:05.175
but he got sick...

24:05.243 --> 24:06.642
and he died.

24:06.711 --> 24:07.871
Really?

24:07.946 --> 24:09.174
Mm-hmm.

24:09.247 --> 24:11.044
Thank you, Lord!

24:11.116 --> 24:13.209
[Speaking Spanish]

24:13.285 --> 24:14.377
You again.

24:16.955 --> 24:22.621
"Steve Ne-bra-ska."

24:22.694 --> 24:23.626
Gracias,

24:23.695 --> 24:24.627
De nada,

24:24.696 --> 24:26.630
You're like a god around here.

24:26.698 --> 24:28.131
I guess they like me.

24:28.200 --> 24:29.633
I'd say that.

24:29.701 --> 24:31.430
Want to know a secret?

24:31.503 --> 24:33.801
Yeah, sure.

24:33.872 --> 24:37.501
I have never paid for
a taco here once...ever.

24:37.576 --> 24:39.737
That's a secret?

24:39.811 --> 24:41.904
It's safe with me.

24:42.981 --> 24:45.415
So how did you
wind up in Mexico?

24:45.484 --> 24:47.042
You got family down here?

24:47.118 --> 24:48.449
No.

24:48.520 --> 24:49.953
Where are they?

24:51.690 --> 24:52.782
Who?

24:52.858 --> 24:55.156
Your family.
Where are they?

24:55.227 --> 24:56.421
Oh, them.

24:56.495 --> 24:58.156
They're, um...

24:58.230 --> 25:01.358
they're, um...
they're in the...

25:01.433 --> 25:03.958
I don't really know
where they are.

25:04.035 --> 25:05.764
They're just kind of, um...

25:10.308 --> 25:11.240
Steve.

25:11.309 --> 25:12.298
Hmm?

25:12.377 --> 25:13.605
Steve.

25:13.678 --> 25:15.578
Steve. Steve.

25:15.647 --> 25:16.739
Steve.

25:16.815 --> 25:17.873
Steve.

25:20.886 --> 25:22.877
Thpppt!

25:22.954 --> 25:23.886
[Laughing]

25:23.955 --> 25:25.889
So you're all alone here?

25:25.957 --> 25:28.255
Well, you're here now.

25:28.326 --> 25:29.759
Well, yes, I am.

25:29.828 --> 25:31.386
And thank God for that.

25:31.463 --> 25:33.397
So, what do you think,
Nebraska?

25:33.465 --> 25:35.558
Want to be a New York Yankee?

25:38.470 --> 25:40.062
Would I make some money?

25:40.138 --> 25:41.571
Would you make some money?

25:41.640 --> 25:45.076
You'll be one of the richest men
in the world.

25:45.143 --> 25:46.405
You're King Kong.

25:46.478 --> 25:47.740
You've got it all.

25:47.812 --> 25:49.973
New York's gonna go
crazy for you.

25:51.082 --> 25:53.016
I've never been to New York.

25:53.084 --> 25:56.076
I don't know anybody there.
Where would I live?

25:56.154 --> 25:57.519
You live anywhere you choose.

25:57.589 --> 26:00.353
You can stay with me
if you want to.

26:00.425 --> 26:01.756
No problem, Steve.

26:05.430 --> 26:07.227
O.K. Let's do it.

26:07.299 --> 26:08.231
That's it!

26:08.300 --> 26:09.232
Uh-huh.

26:09.301 --> 26:10.768
Hey, hey!

26:10.835 --> 26:14.066
Oh, man!
This is the greatest!

26:14.139 --> 26:15.197
All right.

26:15.273 --> 26:17.707
I'll go to the hotel,
make a call,

26:17.776 --> 26:19.209
get the ball rolling tonight.

26:19.277 --> 26:21.711
A few quick questions,
standard stuff.

26:21.780 --> 26:22.712
O.K.

26:22.781 --> 26:24.214
You don't throw up...

26:24.282 --> 26:26.113
or run away or anything?

26:26.184 --> 26:27.617
Como?

26:27.686 --> 26:28.948
Huh? What?

26:29.020 --> 26:30.487
What do you mean?

26:30.555 --> 26:33.490
I mean, you don't
get extra nervous...

26:33.558 --> 26:37.494
Steve, Yankee Stadium is different
from what you’ve ever played in.

26:37.562 --> 26:40.497
It's a lot of people.
It's not like here.

26:40.565 --> 26:41.998
Now, that doesn't bother you?

26:42.067 --> 26:43.398
No. People, that's O.K.

26:43.468 --> 26:45.902
I can play in front
of a million people.

26:45.971 --> 26:47.404
I don't see the people,

26:47.472 --> 26:49.406
just the plate,
the glove, the throw.

26:49.474 --> 26:51.032
You are beautiful!

26:51.109 --> 26:53.634
And that's it.
No problems, right?

26:53.712 --> 26:55.236
Nothing else bothers you?

26:55.313 --> 26:57.178
Yeah, one thing bothers me.

26:57.248 --> 26:58.681
All these questions
you're asking.

26:58.750 --> 27:00.012
I don't like questions.

27:00.085 --> 27:02.986
I don't like
to answer questions.

27:03.054 --> 27:04.487
Steve, no more questions,

27:04.556 --> 27:06.023
just statements.

27:06.091 --> 27:08.025
We're going to New York!

27:08.093 --> 27:09.822
It's gonna be great!

27:09.961 --> 27:12.429
Ron, I'm on a different phone.
Don’t yell.

27:12.497 --> 27:16.263
It has nothing to do with the phone.
I like yelling.

27:16.334 --> 27:18.859
I have found
the most astounding ballplayer

27:18.937 --> 27:20.370
that ever lived.

27:20.438 --> 27:22.372
I've never seen
anything like it.

27:22.440 --> 27:24.374
He can hit, pitch.
It's extraordinary.

27:24.442 --> 27:26.672
I stake my reputation on it.

27:26.745 --> 27:27.871
Your reputation?

27:27.946 --> 27:30.107
Now that's a laugh.

27:30.181 --> 27:31.648
Whatever.
Wait'll you see him.

27:31.716 --> 27:32.944
You'll change your mind.

27:33.018 --> 27:35.680
You're not bringing
anybody back with you.

27:35.754 --> 27:37.187
Oh, yes, I am.

27:37.255 --> 27:39.519
You can't stop me.

27:39.591 --> 27:41.388
Oh, yeah? Watch this.

27:41.459 --> 27:44.257
You're fired.

27:44.329 --> 27:45.728
You're firing me?

27:45.797 --> 27:46.923
Yeah.

27:46.998 --> 27:49.899
So I am no longer affiliated
with the Yankees?

27:49.968 --> 27:51.526
You got that one right.

27:51.603 --> 27:53.036
Then he's a free agent.

27:53.104 --> 27:55.732
I can do whatever
I want with him.

27:55.807 --> 27:58.139
Marry him if you want to.

27:58.209 --> 28:00.837
This is an important moment
of my life.

28:00.912 --> 28:02.937
We need someone to document it.

28:03.014 --> 28:05.414
A Mexican attorney just
happened to come in.

28:05.483 --> 28:06.916
Would you come here, sir?

28:06.985 --> 28:09.419
I'm talking to the
Yankee general manager.

28:09.487 --> 28:10.886
He has just fired me,

28:10.955 --> 28:13.856
which means he has no rights
to Steve Nebraska.

28:13.925 --> 28:16.359
Steve Nebraska can go
to the highest bidder.

28:16.428 --> 28:17.895
Do you understand?

28:17.962 --> 28:18.894
Si,

28:18.963 --> 28:20.362
There. Documented
by an attorney,

28:20.432 --> 28:21.865
you fat bastard!

28:21.933 --> 28:23.867
Sir, your party has hung up.

28:23.935 --> 28:25.368
Huh? Where'd he go?

28:25.437 --> 28:26.870
I don't know, sir.

28:26.938 --> 28:30.135
Did he hear
the fat bastard part?

28:30.208 --> 28:34.372
[Singing Take Me Out
To The Ball Game In Spanish]

28:34.446 --> 28:35.413
Adios,

28:35.480 --> 28:36.412
Bye.

28:36.481 --> 28:37.413
Bye!

28:39.784 --> 28:41.547
Ha ha! Goodbye.

28:50.895 --> 28:52.954
Goodbye!

28:53.031 --> 28:55.829
~ Do you know the way
to San Jose? ~

28:55.900 --> 28:57.993
~ I've been away so long ~

28:58.069 --> 29:00.435
~ I may go wrong
and lose my way ~

29:00.505 --> 29:02.132
~ Do you know
the way... ~~

29:02.207 --> 29:04.141
You're singing
a little too loud.

29:04.209 --> 29:05.642
I'm singing too loudly?

29:05.710 --> 29:07.143
And talking too loudly.

29:07.212 --> 29:08.645
And talking too loudly?

29:08.713 --> 29:11.273
Could you turn that thing down?

29:11.349 --> 29:12.839
[Shouting] Know why that happens?

29:12.917 --> 29:15.852
It's because you got
the earphones in your ears,

29:15.920 --> 29:18.354
and then you can't
hear yourself speak.

29:18.423 --> 29:20.983
~ In a week or 2
they make you a star ~~

29:21.059 --> 29:25.860
[Humming]

29:29.434 --> 29:30.867
What was that?

29:30.935 --> 29:33.130
I think it's her phone number.

29:33.204 --> 29:35.798
You didn't even look.
How do you know?

29:35.874 --> 29:38.365
I'm pretty sure
it's her phone number.

29:38.443 --> 29:39.876
Just out of curiosity,

29:39.944 --> 29:42.378
let's look at it.

29:42.447 --> 29:43.880
I'm curious.

29:43.948 --> 29:45.245
[Humming]

29:45.316 --> 29:48.877
~ Away from home ~~

29:48.953 --> 29:51.888
That must happen
to you a lot, huh?

29:53.958 --> 29:56.893
I have a whole box of them.

29:57.962 --> 29:59.395
Celina.

29:59.464 --> 30:00.897
Gloria.

30:02.300 --> 30:04.002
~ Ba-ba-ba-ba ~~

30:04.135 --> 30:05.397
That's terrific news, Cliff.

30:05.470 --> 30:08.200
And who's Peter O'Malley
sending?

30:08.273 --> 30:10.173
Al?

30:10.241 --> 30:12.402
Al?

30:15.346 --> 30:16.608
Al!

30:16.681 --> 30:18.512
I got to go.

30:18.583 --> 30:19.982
I'll call you tonight.

30:20.051 --> 30:21.109
Steve!

30:21.186 --> 30:22.676
Al!

30:22.754 --> 30:24.415
Steve.

30:24.489 --> 30:28.255
Have I got great news for you.

30:28.326 --> 30:29.850
Don't do that again.

30:29.928 --> 30:31.361
I thought you’d left.

30:31.429 --> 30:32.418
Leave you?

30:32.497 --> 30:34.692
I wouldn't count on it.

30:34.766 --> 30:36.290
Listen, things are heating up.

30:36.367 --> 30:38.301
Representatives from
every major league team

30:38.369 --> 30:40.803
are coming here tomorrow
to watch us play.

30:40.872 --> 30:44.467
But I thought I was
going to be a Yankee.

30:44.542 --> 30:46.442
You still could be a Yankee.

30:46.511 --> 30:48.945
You could be a Yankee, a Brave,

30:49.013 --> 30:50.412
whoever likes us the best.

30:50.481 --> 30:53.450
You're still going to get to pitch
at Yankee Stadium.

30:53.518 --> 30:55.986
I got the place for two hours.

30:56.054 --> 30:59.114
I don't have a lot of strings,
but I pulled them all.

30:59.190 --> 31:00.623
~ I love New York~

31:00.692 --> 31:02.887
~The buildings are very tall ~

31:02.961 --> 31:04.394
~ I love New York~

31:04.462 --> 31:07.693
~The people probably look
real small from up there ~

31:07.765 --> 31:09.323
~ I love New York~

31:09.400 --> 31:11.630
~ I love New York~

31:11.703 --> 31:14.297
~ Look at all the lights
and all the people ~

31:14.372 --> 31:16.897
~ And there's a man wearing
a dress in New York~

31:16.975 --> 31:18.704
~We love New York~

31:18.776 --> 31:20.641
~ It's my new home ~

31:20.712 --> 31:23.340
~ I love NewYork~~

31:23.414 --> 31:24.642
Right here.

31:24.716 --> 31:26.547
Here. Here.

31:30.021 --> 31:31.921
Take whatever...

31:31.990 --> 31:33.924
Hey, good luck.

31:33.992 --> 31:34.924
Thanks.

31:34.993 --> 31:37.427
Listen, I got
a beautiful sister.

31:37.495 --> 31:38.928
Here's her number.

31:38.997 --> 31:40.430
Give her a call.

31:40.498 --> 31:41.430
Thanks.

31:41.499 --> 31:43.433
Come on, Al.

31:48.006 --> 31:49.439
Look who’s back.

31:49.507 --> 31:51.441
Ah, Mr. Percolo,
welcome back.

31:51.509 --> 31:52.942
Hi, Danny.

31:53.011 --> 31:54.444
How you doing?

31:54.512 --> 31:56.673
Danny, Steve Nebraska,

31:56.748 --> 31:59.114
maybe the greatest ballplayer
that ever lived.

31:59.183 --> 32:03.051
Steve's staying with me
for a while, so be nice.

32:03.121 --> 32:04.053
That's wonderful.

32:04.122 --> 32:05.885
You're a ballplayer, huh?

32:05.957 --> 32:07.390
Who do you play for?

32:07.458 --> 32:09.892
We don't know yet,
but whoever it is,

32:09.961 --> 32:12.395
Al says we're gonna be rich.

32:12.463 --> 32:14.397
Ha ha. Come on.

32:14.465 --> 32:15.397
Rich!

32:15.466 --> 32:16.899
Come on.

32:22.974 --> 32:24.908
It's not a good idea

32:24.976 --> 32:27.410
to say you’re gonna be rich.

32:27.478 --> 32:29.412
It always works out badly.

32:30.982 --> 32:32.916
Well...

32:32.984 --> 32:34.417
let's go back down there

32:34.485 --> 32:37.420
and tell him that we're
not gonna be rich.

32:37.488 --> 32:38.921
It's too late now.

32:38.990 --> 32:40.423
People always believe

32:40.491 --> 32:42.425
the first thing they hear.

32:44.362 --> 32:48.992
[Saxophonist Practices Scales]

32:58.443 --> 33:00.377
Home sweet home.

33:00.445 --> 33:01.878
Wow.

33:01.946 --> 33:04.881
Would you look at this place?

33:05.950 --> 33:07.383
It's huge.

33:08.453 --> 33:10.887
It's got a view and everything.

33:10.955 --> 33:12.388
It's of another building,

33:12.457 --> 33:14.891
but I guess it's a view.

33:14.959 --> 33:16.449
Nobody broke in.

33:18.963 --> 33:20.396
I feel rich already.

33:20.465 --> 33:22.899
Take the bedroom.
I'll sleep out here.

33:22.967 --> 33:24.400
I'm all right here.

33:24.469 --> 33:26.903
I don't want you
screwing up your back.

33:26.971 --> 33:28.404
Take the bedroom.

33:28.473 --> 33:29.405
O.K.

33:32.977 --> 33:35.468
Look at the size of this bed!

33:35.546 --> 33:36.979
Don't jump on that!

33:37.048 --> 33:38.982
That's not gonna hold!

33:39.050 --> 33:40.415
I'm sorry.

33:41.986 --> 33:44.147
Where's that box
of phone numbers

33:44.222 --> 33:45.689
I had on the airplane?

33:47.492 --> 33:48.925
I can't believe that people

33:48.993 --> 33:51.928
are gonna be getting laid
in this apartment,

33:51.996 --> 33:53.930
and I'm not one of them.

33:55.500 --> 33:57.525
[Snoring]

34:01.005 --> 34:03.599
Go away.

34:03.674 --> 34:05.539
[Mumbling]

34:06.611 --> 34:07.908
Put it down.

34:09.447 --> 34:10.880
I hate you!

34:11.949 --> 34:13.882
I can't stop!

34:18.022 --> 34:20.489
Aah!

34:27.465 --> 34:28.431
Good morning.

34:28.498 --> 34:31.400
I want to thank you all
for coming here

34:31.469 --> 34:33.027
on such short notice.

34:33.103 --> 34:36.039
But, boy, have we got
a beautiful day for this.

34:36.107 --> 34:38.632
Jesus Christ,
he's going to make speeches now.

34:38.708 --> 34:40.643
Now in my opinion,

34:40.710 --> 34:43.145
you're about to see
the best ballplayer

34:43.214 --> 34:44.647
I've ever seen,

34:44.715 --> 34:46.148
buyout be the judge.

34:46.217 --> 34:47.650
No more talk.

34:47.717 --> 34:49.150
Time to see him.

34:49.219 --> 34:50.915
Ladies and gentlemen...

34:50.987 --> 34:53.081
Steve Nebraska,

34:53.157 --> 34:54.920
right here.

34:57.628 --> 34:59.357
Come out now!

35:00.431 --> 35:02.058
Where is he?

35:04.702 --> 35:06.363
Where is he, Al?

35:06.437 --> 35:08.871
There we go, Steve Nebraska!

35:08.940 --> 35:10.874
Come on out.

35:10.942 --> 35:12.705
Check the turnpike, Al.

35:12.777 --> 35:15.371
- Ha ha ha!
- Ha ha ha!

35:17.949 --> 35:19.746
I'm sure.

35:19.817 --> 35:21.375
Where is he? Steve!

35:21.452 --> 35:24.250
There he is.
Just getting his shoes on.

35:24.322 --> 35:25.880
Steve Nebraska!

35:26.958 --> 35:28.585
Take a few warmups,

35:28.659 --> 35:31.059
and let me know
when you're ready.

35:31.129 --> 35:32.562
I don't need to warm up.

35:32.630 --> 35:34.063
Are you sure?

35:34.132 --> 35:35.895
He's all warmed up.

35:35.967 --> 35:38.401
I guess that's what
he was doing.

35:38.469 --> 35:40.027
O.K., now,

35:40.104 --> 35:41.901
a pitcher of Steve's quality

35:41.973 --> 35:44.703
has got to have somebody
to pitch to.

35:44.775 --> 35:48.734
Can you believe who's
going to help us out here?

35:48.813 --> 35:50.246
One of the greats...

35:50.314 --> 35:52.145
Keith Hernandez!

35:53.484 --> 35:54.416
Keith!

35:54.485 --> 35:57.010
Thanks a lot for coming.

35:57.088 --> 35:58.851
Right up there.

35:58.923 --> 36:00.356
O.K., here we go!

36:01.626 --> 36:03.059
Where's my money?

36:03.127 --> 36:04.526
I don't have it on me.

36:04.595 --> 36:06.028
I don't do this

36:06.097 --> 36:08.031
unless I'm paid
up-front.

36:08.099 --> 36:10.863
I'll give you
the money, O.K.?

36:10.935 --> 36:13.631
O.K.

36:13.704 --> 36:15.365
Steve, fire when ready.

36:33.791 --> 36:35.281
Excuse me...

36:35.359 --> 36:38.294
I, um, I don't know
what those signals mean.

36:38.362 --> 36:40.887
Then why are you shaking
your head no?

36:40.965 --> 36:42.398
Uh, I don't know.

36:42.466 --> 36:44.627
You're supposed
to shake no, right?

36:44.702 --> 36:47.398
Hey, just throw
what you want to throw.

36:47.471 --> 36:50.031
O.K., all right.

37:04.522 --> 37:06.183
Ooh!

37:06.257 --> 37:07.690
Holy mackerel!

37:10.661 --> 37:13.459
I've never seen
anything like this.

37:13.531 --> 37:16.466
How much do you
want to go on this kid?

37:16.534 --> 37:17.967
Whatever it takes.

37:18.035 --> 37:19.525
You got it.

37:24.709 --> 37:27.872
Man, did you see that?

37:32.583 --> 37:34.881
Strike 3. He's out.

37:34.952 --> 37:37.785
Keith, step out a minute,
will you, please?

37:37.855 --> 37:39.379
Larry, did you clock him?

37:39.457 --> 37:40.890
It's broken.

37:40.958 --> 37:43.893
It says 6 then 7 then 9.

37:43.961 --> 37:46.395
It had to be faster than that.

37:46.464 --> 37:47.522
That's 109.

37:47.598 --> 37:49.395
Oh, no, it can't be.

37:49.467 --> 37:51.401
This thing doesn't go over 100.

37:51.469 --> 37:52.902
See the asterisk?

37:52.970 --> 37:54.403
That means you've reached 100,

37:54.472 --> 37:56.838
then you've got
your number... 109.

37:58.409 --> 37:59.842
God damn.

37:59.910 --> 38:02.003
If all Steve did was pitch,

38:02.079 --> 38:03.512
that would be pretty good,

38:03.581 --> 38:05.572
but he likes to hit, too.

38:05.650 --> 38:08.050
I wanted to give him
the best competition,

38:08.119 --> 38:10.417
so to help us out...

38:10.488 --> 38:12.422
Bret Saberhagen.

38:13.891 --> 38:16.359
Bret, thanks a lot.
I appreciate it.

38:16.427 --> 38:17.860
I haven't been paid yet.

38:17.928 --> 38:19.862
What is it with you guys?

38:19.930 --> 38:21.363
It's in the mail.

38:21.432 --> 38:23.866
Keith said I'm supposed
to get paid first.

38:23.934 --> 38:25.868
He's just a mistrustful fellow.

38:25.936 --> 38:27.369
That was the agreement.

38:27.438 --> 38:30.373
$9 million, he needs my money.

38:40.818 --> 38:42.615
Whoa!

38:49.627 --> 38:51.254
O.K. If I switch?

38:51.329 --> 38:52.796
Do whatever you want.

38:57.435 --> 39:00.004
Well, there you have it.

39:00.137 --> 39:02.071
Where'd this guy come from?

39:02.139 --> 39:05.370
The bidding's going to go
differently than you're used to.

39:05.443 --> 39:09.106
All sealed bids will be
delivered to me

39:09.180 --> 39:10.875
within one hour.

39:10.948 --> 39:13.178
How come you’re
accepting the bids?

39:13.250 --> 39:14.877
Who authorized you?

39:14.952 --> 39:16.214
Steve did.

39:16.287 --> 39:18.278
Remember when you let me go?

39:18.356 --> 39:20.881
He hired me.

39:30.434 --> 39:32.129
Yeah, that's fair.

39:34.705 --> 39:36.104
Yankee letterhead.

39:36.173 --> 39:38.164
Look at Steinbrenner.

39:38.242 --> 39:39.174
Poker faced.

39:42.446 --> 39:43.879
Ladies and gentlemen...

39:43.948 --> 39:46.382
thank you for waiting.

39:46.450 --> 39:49.248
We're ready to announce
now the winning bid.

39:49.320 --> 39:51.754
We want to thank
you all very much.

39:51.822 --> 39:52.789
Uh...

39:52.857 --> 39:54.882
I've never done this before.

39:54.959 --> 39:58.019
I'm a scout, not a speaker.

39:58.095 --> 40:00.825
I'm a little nervous at this.

40:00.898 --> 40:03.389
I want to thank
all of the clubs.

40:03.467 --> 40:06.527
All of the bids were
very, very respectable,

40:06.604 --> 40:08.037
but like a baseball game,

40:08.105 --> 40:10.096
somebody has to win,
and somebody did.

40:10.174 --> 40:14.804
With a bid of $55 million

40:14.879 --> 40:17.814
over the next four years,

40:17.882 --> 40:20.282
Steve Nebraska
is very proud to be

40:20.351 --> 40:22.148
a New York Yankee!

40:22.219 --> 40:25.313
Thank you for coming, and
we'll see you on the field.

40:25.389 --> 40:27.482
$55 million after one tryout?

40:27.558 --> 40:29.458
How can you justify that?

40:29.527 --> 40:31.927
I have to go
with my gut instinct.

40:31.996 --> 40:33.429
After what I saw today,

40:33.497 --> 40:35.556
he's worth every penny of it.

40:35.633 --> 40:37.157
So he's pitching right away?

40:37.234 --> 40:40.431
He's pitching as soon as
we get him in uniform.

40:40.504 --> 40:43.302
That's not the way
the deal was structured.

40:43.374 --> 40:45.137
It isn't?

40:45.209 --> 40:47.803
Uh, Mr. Wilson may
not be informed,

40:47.878 --> 40:51.473
but the teams were in agreement
that no matter who got Steve,

40:51.549 --> 40:53.813
because we're far
into this season,

40:53.884 --> 40:57.547
Steve doesn't want to take
any blame or credit,

40:57.621 --> 41:01.079
so he would get a fresh start
next year as a Yankee.

41:01.158 --> 41:03.388
Well, just a minute.
What are you saying?

41:03.461 --> 41:05.986
We can't play him this year?

41:06.063 --> 41:07.496
Stop taking my picture.

41:07.565 --> 41:09.260
You got 32 already.

41:09.333 --> 41:12.894
Mr. Wilson is asking
what would happen

41:12.970 --> 41:14.403
if the New York Yankees

41:14.472 --> 41:16.565
would get into the World Series?

41:16.640 --> 41:18.904
- Ha ha ha!
- Ha ha ha!

41:20.478 --> 41:22.207
Why are they laughing, Al?

41:22.279 --> 41:24.747
I'm going to make
a deal right now.

41:24.815 --> 41:27.249
If the Yankees get
in the World Series,

41:27.318 --> 41:29.912
Steve Nebraska
pitches the first game.

41:29.987 --> 41:31.249
All right?

41:31.322 --> 41:33.916
Does that mean I pitch
the first game?

41:33.991 --> 41:36.425
It can never happen.
Don't worry.

41:37.661 --> 41:40.960
How many years
did you play in Mexico?

41:41.031 --> 41:42.965
Steve, where do you live?

41:43.033 --> 41:44.625
Um, I don't know.

41:44.702 --> 41:46.693
Al, Al, Al, Al!

41:46.770 --> 41:48.738
Al, Al, Al, Al!

41:48.806 --> 41:50.706
All right, all right.

41:50.774 --> 41:53.174
Folks, it's been
a very long morning.

41:53.244 --> 41:55.940
He's tired.
Just give him a break.

41:56.013 --> 41:57.537
No more pictures.

42:04.955 --> 42:07.389
Put him down!
Put him down!

42:08.959 --> 42:09.948
Now, gentlemen...

42:11.462 --> 42:12.793
All right.

42:15.399 --> 42:17.560
I just want to reiterate

42:17.635 --> 42:19.899
on behalf
of George Steinbrenner...

42:20.037 --> 42:21.402
O.K., it's official.

42:21.472 --> 42:22.734
[Applause]

42:22.806 --> 42:24.706
Congratulations, Steve.

42:25.809 --> 42:29.108
Al, I want to talk
to you for a minute.

42:29.179 --> 42:30.908
Be right back, kiddo.

42:32.483 --> 42:35.418
Al, we're going to need
a little something from you.

42:35.486 --> 42:37.954
Your lawyer didn't tell you
about the letter?

42:38.022 --> 42:41.321
What are you talking about?
What letter?

42:41.392 --> 42:42.825
Before we pay him,

42:42.893 --> 42:45.418
we'll need a letter
from a psychiatrist

42:45.496 --> 42:46.929
saying that he's all right.

42:46.997 --> 42:48.931
You already paid him the money.

42:48.999 --> 42:50.398
He just signed the contract.

42:50.467 --> 42:53.436
That was ceremonial.
Your lawyer knows this.

42:53.504 --> 42:56.098
This is the most
amount of money

42:56.173 --> 42:57.868
anybody has every been paid.

42:57.942 --> 42:59.375
Mr. Steinbrenner
wants assurances

42:59.443 --> 43:02.276
that Steve won't flake out
like your other picks.

43:02.346 --> 43:04.644
I find this insulting.
This is ridiculous.

43:04.715 --> 43:07.115
Did you see him pick up
that photographer?

43:07.184 --> 43:08.378
So what?

43:08.452 --> 43:10.044
I told him to.

43:10.120 --> 43:13.055
Then I told him to put him down,
which he did.

43:13.123 --> 43:15.785
I find this very insulting.

43:15.859 --> 43:18.123
I'll have the letter tomorrow.

43:18.195 --> 43:21.653
We can set you up
with a doctor if you like.

43:21.732 --> 43:23.962
My sister was in the field.

43:24.034 --> 43:25.524
As long as they're qualified.

43:25.603 --> 43:27.537
Well, of course
they'll be qualified.

43:27.605 --> 43:29.470
I'm not an idiot.

43:29.540 --> 43:31.599
" Physicians..."

43:31.675 --> 43:33.233
physicians...

43:33.310 --> 43:35.244
plastic surgery...

43:35.312 --> 43:36.404
anesthetic...

43:36.480 --> 43:37.412
dietary...

43:37.481 --> 43:38.914
psychiatry...

43:38.983 --> 43:40.348
affiliated...

43:40.417 --> 43:42.510
"Dr. H. Aaron!"

43:42.586 --> 43:43.917
Oh, boy!

43:43.988 --> 43:46.923
Hammering Hank, yes, indeed.

43:50.494 --> 43:51.654
Hey, Steve.

43:51.729 --> 43:54.459
Save a little
of that appetite for lunch.

43:57.434 --> 43:58.366
Hello?

43:58.435 --> 44:00.027
Dr. H. Aaron, please.

44:00.104 --> 44:01.594
This is she.

44:01.672 --> 44:02.866
You're kidding.

44:03.941 --> 44:06.375
I'd like to come
see you right now.

44:06.443 --> 44:07.876
Is that a possibility?

44:07.945 --> 44:09.378
Who am I speaking to?

44:09.446 --> 44:12.677
I'm Al Percolo, and I'm with
the New York Yankees.

44:12.750 --> 44:14.684
Would you like an appointment?

44:14.752 --> 44:16.185
I'd like one now.

44:16.253 --> 44:19.188
If you're still at that address
in the Yellow Pages,

44:19.256 --> 44:20.883
I could scoot over now.

44:20.958 --> 44:22.892
Is this an emergency?

44:22.960 --> 44:24.621
Well...

44:26.764 --> 44:27.788
yes, yes.

44:27.865 --> 44:29.298
Yes, it is.

44:29.366 --> 44:31.391
I'll see you in 45 minutes.

44:31.468 --> 44:32.901
O.K., we'll waste
a little...

44:32.970 --> 44:36.462
Well, we'll see you
in 45 minutes.

44:37.541 --> 44:39.406
Fantastic.

44:39.476 --> 44:40.909
I did it.

44:40.978 --> 44:42.411
10 minutes with this broad,

44:42.479 --> 44:44.310
we got the letter.

44:46.483 --> 44:47.415
You know, last night

44:47.484 --> 44:48.917
you were really having

44:48.986 --> 44:50.920
quite a little nightmare.

44:50.988 --> 44:52.421
No, I wasn't.

44:52.489 --> 44:53.421
You weren't?

44:53.490 --> 44:55.424
Maybe it was me.

44:56.493 --> 44:57.357
Yep.

44:57.428 --> 44:59.362
Cranham Center.
This is it.

45:14.445 --> 45:16.879
What's she going to do, Al?

45:16.947 --> 45:18.380
It's like a physical,

45:18.449 --> 45:19.882
only mental.

45:28.459 --> 45:30.393
[Sniffling]

45:37.835 --> 45:39.268
Was that the doctor?

45:39.336 --> 45:40.769
Gee, I hope not.

45:42.473 --> 45:44.566
Good morning.
I'm Dr. Aaron.

45:44.641 --> 45:45.835
Mr. Percolo?

45:45.909 --> 45:47.399
I'm Mr. Percolo.

45:47.478 --> 45:50.447
Uh, could I talk to you
for a minute?

45:50.514 --> 45:51.446
Of course.

45:51.515 --> 45:52.948
I'll be right back.

45:56.520 --> 45:57.578
[Sniffs]

46:01.058 --> 46:04.186
I appreciate you seeing us
on such short notice.

46:04.261 --> 46:07.196
Before we start,
may I ask you a question?

46:07.264 --> 46:08.196
Sure.

46:08.265 --> 46:09.698
You licensed?

46:09.767 --> 46:11.200
Am I licensed?

46:11.268 --> 46:13.566
Yes, I am licensed.

46:13.637 --> 46:15.571
Would it be rude to...

46:15.639 --> 46:17.072
to see a diploma?

46:17.141 --> 46:19.302
Anything you can show me?

46:19.376 --> 46:21.867
No one's asked
to see my diploma

46:21.945 --> 46:24.311
since I began the practice.

46:24.381 --> 46:25.746
No.

46:25.816 --> 46:27.306
Yes.

46:27.384 --> 46:28.783
It's on the wall.

46:28.852 --> 46:29.784
Those?

46:29.853 --> 46:30.785
Mm-hmm.

46:30.854 --> 46:32.788
I'll take a quick look.

46:37.961 --> 46:39.394
Harvard?

46:39.463 --> 46:40.896
Whoa, whoa!

46:40.964 --> 46:41.896
Great.

46:41.965 --> 46:43.398
That's the real one?

46:43.467 --> 46:45.401
Yes, that's the real one.

46:46.970 --> 46:48.904
Well, this is very impressive.

46:48.972 --> 46:50.906
Anything with a picture on it?

46:50.974 --> 46:52.407
Is this a joke?

46:52.476 --> 46:53.909
Is this a joke?

46:53.977 --> 46:56.411
I just want
to make sure it's you.

46:56.480 --> 46:58.209
It's got to be you.

46:58.282 --> 46:59.840
You can't put up a diploma
if it's not yours.

46:59.917 --> 47:01.544
That's a felony, isn't it?

47:01.618 --> 47:04.348
Why don’t you tell me
what's going on?

47:04.421 --> 47:07.356
The kid sitting out there,
Steve Nebraska,

47:07.424 --> 47:08.857
is probably the best
baseball player

47:08.926 --> 47:10.450
that ever lived.

47:10.527 --> 47:13.462
He has just signed a deal
with the New York Yankees

47:13.530 --> 47:16.522
that's gonna make him
almost $60 million.

47:16.600 --> 47:19.034
When you pay
that kind of money,

47:19.102 --> 47:22.037
you want to be assured
that everything's gonna be O.K.

47:22.105 --> 47:25.040
They just need a couple of sentences
on a letterhead

47:25.108 --> 47:26.541
that they believe that says

47:26.610 --> 47:28.544
he's not gonna shoot anybody

47:28.612 --> 47:32.048
or run away
or throw up on the mound.

47:32.115 --> 47:34.777
Tell me again what this letter
should say?

47:34.852 --> 47:36.376
Address it
to George Steinbrenner.

47:36.453 --> 47:37.886
You just want to say...

47:37.955 --> 47:40.389
who you are
in a sentence or two.

47:40.457 --> 47:42.391
Say that you went to Harvard...

47:42.459 --> 47:44.484
is the right thing to say.

47:44.561 --> 47:46.654
And then say Steve's not nuts,

47:46.730 --> 47:48.129
not gonna run away.

47:48.198 --> 47:49.893
Good deal there.
Congratulations.

47:49.967 --> 47:51.400
Then you'll sign your name.

47:51.468 --> 47:54.403
If you want to include
a xerox of the diploma,

47:54.471 --> 47:55.904
that would be helpful.

47:55.973 --> 47:59.272
And you could put, " P.S.
Sorry about Billy Martin."

47:59.343 --> 48:00.640
Billy Martin?

48:00.711 --> 48:02.838
Just a guy he kept firing

48:02.913 --> 48:04.346
till he finally died.

48:05.582 --> 48:07.516
Why don't I talk to Steve,

48:07.584 --> 48:10.144
and then we can
talk after that?

48:10.220 --> 48:12.654
You don't want to do
the letter first?

48:12.723 --> 48:14.953
I don't think so.

48:18.795 --> 48:20.820
These smell so good.

48:20.898 --> 48:23.093
Yes, it's nice.

48:28.939 --> 48:30.702
What are you doing?

48:30.774 --> 48:32.207
What are you doing?

48:32.276 --> 48:33.709
It's a physical.

48:33.777 --> 48:34.709
What physical?

48:34.778 --> 48:36.211
Al said that...

48:36.280 --> 48:39.374
I told him
it was like a physical.

48:39.449 --> 48:42.612
Put your pants on.

48:42.686 --> 48:43.675
We're done.

48:43.754 --> 48:46.086
Maybe it would be better,
Mr. Percolo,

48:46.156 --> 48:48.886
if I spoke to Steve alone.

48:48.959 --> 48:50.392
All right.

48:50.460 --> 48:51.392
Um...

48:51.461 --> 48:52.894
I'll be right out here.

48:53.964 --> 48:56.831
I would prefer if Al stayed here

48:56.900 --> 48:59.061
in the room with me.

48:59.136 --> 49:02.970
Well, I'd really rather
talk to you alone.

49:03.040 --> 49:04.974
I know, but I would feel

49:05.042 --> 49:06.475
much more comfortable.

49:06.543 --> 49:07.976
It's his first time,

49:08.045 --> 49:10.377
and he's just a little nervous,

49:10.447 --> 49:11.880
so I'll sit here.

49:11.949 --> 49:14.884
You won't even know
I'm in the room.

49:14.952 --> 49:16.317
I'll disappear.

49:16.386 --> 49:18.183
All right.

49:18.255 --> 49:19.347
All right.

49:20.924 --> 49:22.858
Please sit down, Steve.

49:22.926 --> 49:24.359
Ahem.

49:24.428 --> 49:26.362
So, Steve, where are you from?

49:26.430 --> 49:27.863
I found him in Mexico.

49:27.931 --> 49:29.364
I was asking Steve.

49:29.433 --> 49:30.365
I answered?

49:30.434 --> 49:31.366
Yeah.

49:31.435 --> 49:33.369
So you’re from Mexico?

49:33.437 --> 49:35.371
Uh, no, I'm not from Mexico.

49:35.439 --> 49:38.374
I was just down there
for a couple of years.

49:38.442 --> 49:39.932
And why Mexico?

49:40.010 --> 49:42.877
Because it's, um...

49:42.946 --> 49:44.743
where I went.

49:44.815 --> 49:45.941
Mm-hmm.

49:46.016 --> 49:48.541
You don't remember what
brought you down there?

49:48.618 --> 49:49.550
Uh-uh.

49:49.619 --> 49:50.881
Well...

49:50.954 --> 49:53.889
uh, not, not...

49:53.957 --> 49:57.393
Baseball brought you
down there, didn't it?

49:57.461 --> 49:59.725
Baseball brought me down there.

49:59.796 --> 50:02.924
You really like baseball, hmm?

50:03.000 --> 50:04.058
Yes, ma'am,

50:04.134 --> 50:06.568
it's my favorite thing
in the whole world.

50:06.636 --> 50:08.900
When did you start playing?

50:10.607 --> 50:12.632
Steve, is there
something wrong?

50:14.378 --> 50:16.903
I just, uh...

50:16.980 --> 50:19.073
I don't like
all these questions.

50:19.149 --> 50:21.583
Do you sometimes feel
that there are things

50:21.651 --> 50:24.586
that you try to remember
and can't?

50:24.654 --> 50:26.417
Yeah. No.

50:26.490 --> 50:28.390
I guess so.
I don't know.

50:28.458 --> 50:30.926
You know what I'd like to try?

50:30.994 --> 50:33.428
I'd like to show you
some pictures.

50:33.497 --> 50:36.432
I want you to give me
your immediate response.

50:36.500 --> 50:37.933
Just look at the picture,

50:38.001 --> 50:39.434
and without even thinking,

50:39.503 --> 50:42.404
just tell me
what it means to you.

50:43.974 --> 50:46.442
It's kind of like
a word-association game.

50:46.510 --> 50:47.943
Just look at the picture

50:48.011 --> 50:50.445
and tell me whatever
comes to your mind.

50:52.516 --> 50:53.448
O.K.

50:53.517 --> 50:54.449
Who's that?

50:54.518 --> 50:56.247
These aren't actual people.

50:56.319 --> 50:59.311
Now what does this
look like to you?

50:59.389 --> 51:00.822
That guy's faking it.

51:00.891 --> 51:04.088
You can tell 'cause the doctors
don't look concerned at all.

51:04.161 --> 51:07.392
He's just pretending
to be in a coma.

51:07.464 --> 51:09.193
He knows if he opens his eyes,

51:09.266 --> 51:12.531
he's going to see his bill.

51:12.602 --> 51:14.035
He stays in a coma

51:14.104 --> 51:16.868
so he doesn't have
to pay his bill.

51:16.940 --> 51:18.373
What a great idea.

51:18.442 --> 51:20.410
Mr. Percolo, if you
keep speaking,

51:20.477 --> 51:23.640
I'm going to have to ask you
to step outside.

51:23.713 --> 51:24.907
Sorry.

51:24.981 --> 51:27.814
You know, the medical costs
being what they are...

51:27.884 --> 51:30.114
The next picture, Steve.

51:32.389 --> 51:34.357
These guys are in trouble.

51:34.424 --> 51:37.120
They look like
they're in trouble?

51:37.194 --> 51:39.719
Not yet, but when
that driver gets angry,

51:39.796 --> 51:41.229
and he's going to,

51:41.298 --> 51:43.926
they're all going to start
screaming and crying.

51:44.000 --> 51:45.194
It's just...

51:45.268 --> 51:48.760
It's going to be a mess.

51:54.811 --> 51:55.937
This one?

51:57.747 --> 51:58.975
She sneezed.

52:03.086 --> 52:05.486
Anything else?

52:05.555 --> 52:07.386
Um...

52:07.457 --> 52:09.391
she sneezed by the door.

52:09.459 --> 52:11.051
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

52:14.164 --> 52:17.258
That's Batman.

52:17.334 --> 52:18.767
Batman?

52:18.835 --> 52:21.269
Batman. Sometimes
he goes without his cape.

52:27.310 --> 52:28.242
O.K.

52:28.311 --> 52:30.245
And this is the last one.

52:37.954 --> 52:40.149
[Coughs] Fishing.

52:40.223 --> 52:42.418
Fishing...
two guys fishing.

52:42.492 --> 52:44.619
Very good.
Anything else?

52:47.264 --> 52:48.697
[Sighs]

52:48.765 --> 52:50.460
O.K., let's see.

52:51.701 --> 52:54.135
They're...two guys
fishing for trout.

52:54.204 --> 52:55.569
Very good.

52:55.639 --> 52:57.163
Yeah? Yeah?

52:57.240 --> 52:59.299
Very good.
You did very well.

52:59.376 --> 53:00.308
I did?

53:00.377 --> 53:01.309
Yes, absolutely.

53:01.378 --> 53:04.006
Hey. Ha ha ha.

53:05.215 --> 53:07.274
If you could step outside

53:07.350 --> 53:10.251
while I talk to Mr. Percolo,
then we'll be through.

53:10.320 --> 53:13.721
O.K. All right,
I'll...

53:13.790 --> 53:16.588
[Door Opens And Closes]

53:16.660 --> 53:18.924
He's got some imagination,
doesn't he?

53:18.995 --> 53:20.428
Boy, that coma story.

53:20.497 --> 53:23.489
I never would have thought
that was Batman. He's something.

53:23.567 --> 53:26.502
I'm not going to talk
in complicated medical terms

53:26.570 --> 53:28.765
because it wouldn't
do much good anyway.

53:28.838 --> 53:29.930
Appreciate that.

53:30.006 --> 53:31.940
He's disconnected in some way.

53:32.008 --> 53:33.600
It's very interesting,

53:33.677 --> 53:36.111
but his response
to this picture,

53:36.179 --> 53:38.044
the father and the son,

53:38.114 --> 53:41.049
he didn't recognize
as father and son.

53:41.117 --> 53:43.551
Almost 98% of the people
shown that picture

53:43.620 --> 53:45.554
immediately make
that association.

53:45.622 --> 53:50.150
Hmm. Let me see it
for a second, may I?

53:50.227 --> 53:53.321
I don't think that's
father and son necessarily.

53:53.396 --> 53:56.365
Doesn't that guy look like
a fishing teacher to you?

53:56.433 --> 53:58.264
Whatever.

53:58.335 --> 53:59.768
Um, in any case,

53:59.836 --> 54:02.361
his responses to
the other pictures,

54:02.439 --> 54:06.034
they were pretty much
showing confused emotions.

54:06.109 --> 54:09.545
It's obvious Steve's not in touch
with a part of himself.

54:09.613 --> 54:12.548
That's one reason why he's
such a good ballplayer.

54:12.616 --> 54:15.050
He's thinking of nothing
but hitting the ball.

54:15.118 --> 54:16.551
And pitching the ball.

54:16.620 --> 54:20.056
You should see.
Strike after strike, like a machine.

54:20.123 --> 54:21.556
It's just...
It's great.

54:21.625 --> 54:23.559
Well, O.K.,
interesting stuff.

54:23.627 --> 54:26.061
Now, do I wait for the letter

54:26.129 --> 54:29.064
or do you want to fax this over?

54:29.132 --> 54:32.568
Well, Mr. Percolo,
I feel I can't give him a letter

54:32.636 --> 54:35.696
that says he should play,
because I don't think he should.

54:35.772 --> 54:38.138
You got to give him the letter.

54:38.208 --> 54:40.335
We... We need the letter.

54:40.410 --> 54:43.345
Let me try and explain
something to you.

54:43.413 --> 54:46.849
Um, ahem, let's just suppose
that Steve has blocked something,

54:46.916 --> 54:49.851
and then let's imagine he
suddenly remembers it.

54:49.919 --> 54:52.854
If he should do that,
he could become very violent,

54:52.922 --> 54:55.356
to himself and to other people.

54:55.425 --> 54:57.359
He should be in therapy.

54:57.427 --> 54:59.054
He shouldn't be
playing athletics.

54:59.129 --> 55:00.562
He's not playing athletics.

55:00.630 --> 55:03.064
In grammar school,
you play athletics.

55:03.133 --> 55:04.566
He's playing
professional baseball.

55:04.634 --> 55:06.568
Besides, violence is a plus.

55:06.636 --> 55:09.070
You ever see those fellas?
They're huge.

55:09.139 --> 55:11.573
The best ballplayers
never had any memory.

55:11.641 --> 55:13.575
Remember Whitey Ford,
great pitcher?

55:13.643 --> 55:15.577
Know why they
called him Whitey?

55:15.645 --> 55:18.580
He couldn't remember
his real name. No memory.

55:18.648 --> 55:20.047
I could go on...

55:20.116 --> 55:22.550
I really can't do it.
I'm sorry.

55:22.619 --> 55:26.077
Ma'am, listen, I'm not
saying you're wrong, O.K.?

55:26.156 --> 55:27.589
Maybe he's got some problems.

55:27.657 --> 55:29.591
But what are you doing?

55:29.659 --> 55:32.594
He's one of the greatest
ballplayers I've ever seen,

55:32.662 --> 55:34.254
and I've seen them all.

55:34.331 --> 55:35.764
I'll work with you.

55:35.832 --> 55:38.198
I'll bring him
seven days a week.

55:38.268 --> 55:41.203
I'll bring him twice
a day if you need it.

55:41.271 --> 55:43.705
But don't deny him
something that he loves.

55:43.773 --> 55:47.265
Without baseball,
then... then he's got nothing.

55:47.344 --> 55:48.777
And then he'll be,

55:48.845 --> 55:51.780
well, he'll be the guy
you say he is.

55:51.848 --> 55:53.577
He'll just be poor, too.

55:53.650 --> 55:55.584
You would bring him every day?

55:55.652 --> 55:57.085
Every single day.

55:57.153 --> 55:59.587
That'll be an important
part of his life,

55:59.656 --> 56:01.089
his working with you.

56:01.157 --> 56:02.590
The letter's just insurance.

56:02.659 --> 56:04.889
I don't think he'll
play this year anyway.

56:04.961 --> 56:06.895
They won’t get in the series.

56:06.963 --> 56:08.897
Really, he's yours till April.

56:08.965 --> 56:11.490
He'll have lots of therapy
before getting on a field.

56:11.568 --> 56:14.002
We just want him on the roster.

56:14.070 --> 56:16.334
That's why we need the letter.

56:16.406 --> 56:18.397
You got to do it.
Please.

56:18.475 --> 56:20.909
If you promise you’ll
bring him every day,

56:20.977 --> 56:23.241
I'll write a letter
saying he can play.

56:23.313 --> 56:26.749
You give me a letter,
I'll give one back.

56:26.816 --> 56:29.751
You say he can play,
I'll say he'll be here.

56:29.819 --> 56:31.184
I don't need a letter.

56:31.254 --> 56:32.687
This worked out great.

56:32.756 --> 56:35.691
When I saw your name
in the Yellow Pages,

56:35.759 --> 56:37.954
I said,
"This woman's special."

56:38.027 --> 56:40.962
I'll call in the morning,
we'll set up the schedule.

56:41.030 --> 56:43.464
I'll come by early
for the letter.

56:43.533 --> 56:45.967
That's fantastic.

56:46.035 --> 56:48.503
Oh, wait a second.
Wait a second.

56:48.571 --> 56:50.300
I think you should know

56:50.373 --> 56:53.706
it's likely Steve will look
to you as a father figure.

56:53.777 --> 56:56.712
You know what?
It's already started to happen.

56:56.780 --> 56:59.544
I'm trying to fill those shoes.
I'll do my best.

56:59.616 --> 57:01.550
I understand, but this a father

57:01.618 --> 57:04.519
Steve might want to
put a bullet through.

57:06.656 --> 57:08.590
How's he feel about his uncles?

57:08.658 --> 57:11.491
- You know that by looking at those pictures?
- No.

57:11.561 --> 57:14.496
All right,
thanks for the warning.

57:14.564 --> 57:17.897
Uncle Al's got
good news for you. Ha.

57:17.967 --> 57:19.400
You did great.

57:19.469 --> 57:20.902
You think so?

57:20.970 --> 57:23.905
She loves you, wants
to see you every day.

57:23.973 --> 57:27.409
I don't know if I want
to see her every day.

57:27.477 --> 57:30.412
It's a good place to
let out your problems.

57:30.480 --> 57:31.913
I don't know her.

57:31.981 --> 57:35.348
She's a doctor.
Once you pay her, you know her.

57:35.418 --> 57:37.045
~You gotta have ~

57:37.120 --> 57:39.554
~ Heart ~

57:39.622 --> 57:43.388
~ All you really
need is heart ~

57:43.460 --> 57:45.052
~ If you don't have heart ~

57:45.128 --> 57:47.062
~Then you don't get dinner ~

57:47.130 --> 57:49.064
~You gotta have heart ~

57:49.132 --> 57:50.565
~ Ba da da dee ~~

57:50.633 --> 57:53.568
That's a great movie.
It's about baseball.

57:53.636 --> 57:54.568
Damn Yankees,

57:54.637 --> 57:56.070
Damn Yankees,

57:56.139 --> 57:58.073
Al!
Talk to us!

57:58.141 --> 57:59.574
Stop ducking us!

57:59.642 --> 58:01.974
Hey, would you go away, please?

58:02.045 --> 58:03.910
We're trying to eat dinner.

58:03.980 --> 58:05.242
Where's Steve?

58:05.315 --> 58:07.442
He's with me.
Now, good night.

58:07.517 --> 58:09.451
People want to know things.

58:09.519 --> 58:11.453
How about a press conference?

58:11.521 --> 58:14.752
We're not doing a press conference
like Romeo and Juliet,

58:14.824 --> 58:16.985
We'll do it at another time.

58:17.060 --> 58:17.992
What are you doing?

58:18.061 --> 58:19.255
Throwing plates.

58:19.329 --> 58:20.990
You can't do that.

58:21.064 --> 58:23.123
M-M-M-Move!

58:23.199 --> 58:24.257
Aah!

58:24.334 --> 58:25.733
M-M-M-Move!

58:25.802 --> 58:27.599
No! No! No! No!

58:27.670 --> 58:29.661
You can't do that!

58:29.739 --> 58:30.706
Are you nuts?

58:30.773 --> 58:33.970
I didn't mean that.
Don't throw plates.

58:34.043 --> 58:35.408
Please!

58:35.478 --> 58:37.343
No!

58:37.413 --> 58:39.347
No! No! No! No!

58:41.751 --> 58:43.685
I've got a crazy landlady.

58:43.753 --> 58:46.085
She's here throwing things.

58:46.155 --> 58:47.588
She'll kill ya!

58:47.657 --> 58:48.749
More plates!

58:48.825 --> 58:51.055
Oh, no, we're
going to get sued.

58:51.127 --> 58:52.253
They're gone.

58:54.631 --> 58:56.599
You got a knife anywhere?

58:56.666 --> 58:57.598
A what?

58:57.667 --> 58:59.999
- I need a sharp knife.
- Why?

59:00.069 --> 59:02.594
To cut things with.

59:02.672 --> 59:04.367
Oh. Cut what up?

59:04.440 --> 59:07.375
I like to cut my food
with a knife.

59:07.443 --> 59:09.877
We're having spaghetti.
You don't need a knife.

59:09.946 --> 59:12.642
I don't have one in the house.

59:12.715 --> 59:14.876
I'm all out...
I got some there.

59:14.951 --> 59:16.384
That's the woman's upstairs.

59:16.452 --> 59:18.682
It's not right for us
to use them.

59:18.755 --> 59:21.315
She's got emphysema.
So it's a bad idea.

59:21.391 --> 59:23.325
Al, give me a knife.

59:23.393 --> 59:24.826
What happened there?

59:24.894 --> 59:26.828
I don't have a knife.

59:26.896 --> 59:28.329
I can't find one.

59:28.398 --> 59:30.229
Oh, you know what?

59:30.300 --> 59:32.461
Use that.
That'll do for you.

59:33.836 --> 59:35.861
This is a butter knife.

59:35.939 --> 59:39.275
Yeah. A nice one, too.
An ivory handle.

59:39.409 --> 59:41.673
Well, I'm not having butter.

59:41.744 --> 59:43.177
You can change your mind.

59:43.246 --> 59:45.476
You want butter,
you got the right knife.

59:45.548 --> 59:47.982
Go back and sing.
Great. Good.

59:50.787 --> 59:53.654
I got to tell you,
I don't understand it,

59:53.723 --> 59:55.657
I can't see a damn thing.

59:55.725 --> 59:59.024
Don't use the binoculars in the house.
You'll hurt your eyes.

59:59.095 --> 01:00:02.030
For the amount of people who've seen
Steve Nebraska play,

01:00:02.098 --> 01:00:03.531
they're talking about you.

01:00:03.600 --> 01:00:05.534
$55 million dollars,

01:00:05.602 --> 01:00:08.036
What about the rumor he's
under a doctor's care?

01:00:08.104 --> 01:00:09.469
Turn that down.

01:00:09.539 --> 01:00:11.564
How'd they find that out?

01:00:11.641 --> 01:00:14.303
If Steve Nebraska
turned out to be Jimmy Piersall?

01:00:14.377 --> 01:00:15.469
Who's Jimmy Piersall?

01:00:15.545 --> 01:00:17.706
Don't worry, you're not him.

01:00:17.780 --> 01:00:19.372
What did they say?

01:00:19.449 --> 01:00:22.384
Hands down, the fastest
pitcher they've ever seen,

01:00:22.452 --> 01:00:24.249
and the best hitter,

01:00:24.320 --> 01:00:26.254
Mmm, what are you doing?

01:00:26.322 --> 01:00:27.755
They're talking about me.

01:00:27.824 --> 01:00:30.987
We're going to have
to do a press conference.

01:00:31.060 --> 01:00:34.359
Al, why? Come on, you said
I wouldn't have to pitch.

01:00:34.430 --> 01:00:36.990
Well, you're going to pitch
eventually, aren’t you?

01:00:37.066 --> 01:00:40.001
If we don't talk to the press,
they'll keep coming.

01:00:40.069 --> 01:00:42.731
They'll make everything up,
like the doctor.

01:00:42.805 --> 01:00:44.238
But all that's true.

01:00:44.307 --> 01:00:47.504
That's true. But it'll
just get worse and worse.

01:00:47.577 --> 01:00:50.512
Next thing you'll know,
you'll be a defector.

01:00:50.580 --> 01:00:53.014
They'll have you
killing somebody.

01:00:53.082 --> 01:00:55.016
That would be cool.

01:00:55.084 --> 01:00:56.847
What does that mean?

01:00:58.588 --> 01:01:00.249
What does what mean?

01:01:00.323 --> 01:01:02.314
Well, that it's
not cool to, uh...

01:01:02.392 --> 01:01:04.326
No, you don't mean that.

01:01:04.394 --> 01:01:06.328
With the money
they're paying you,

01:01:06.396 --> 01:01:09.331
you can't throw a ball
and go home to sleep.

01:01:09.399 --> 01:01:11.367
You got to talk to the press.

01:01:11.434 --> 01:01:13.800
Maybe it's not worth it.

01:01:13.870 --> 01:01:15.303
Not worth it?

01:01:15.371 --> 01:01:18.204
It works out to
a million dollars a question.

01:01:18.274 --> 01:01:20.708
There's going to be
a million questions,

01:01:20.777 --> 01:01:23.211
and I don't know
all the answers.

01:01:23.279 --> 01:01:25.213
I don't want to look foolish.

01:01:25.281 --> 01:01:27.215
I'll never let that happen.

01:01:27.283 --> 01:01:29.717
We'll go over stuff,
just like the president.

01:01:29.786 --> 01:01:32.254
He wakes up a fool.
They help him.

01:01:32.321 --> 01:01:35.290
We'll go over stuff.
We'll fill in the blanks.

01:01:35.358 --> 01:01:38.885
We'll give you a life
you can be proud of.

01:01:41.164 --> 01:01:42.324
- Shh!
- Shh!

01:01:42.398 --> 01:01:45.333
Uh, ladies and gentlemen,
I'm sorry for the delay.

01:01:45.401 --> 01:01:46.834
You all set?

01:01:46.903 --> 01:01:50.339
Hmm? Yeah. Uh, in your version,
did I go to college?

01:01:50.406 --> 01:01:53.341
Yes. We decided that.
Avery good one.

01:01:53.409 --> 01:01:54.842
Listen to me.

01:01:54.911 --> 01:01:57.345
If they bring up
the therapy at all,

01:01:57.413 --> 01:01:59.108
tell them that, uh,

01:01:59.182 --> 01:02:01.616
tell them it's not you, it's me.

01:02:01.684 --> 01:02:03.618
If they bring up the therapy,

01:02:03.686 --> 01:02:07.122
tell them that you’re
taking me to the doctor.

01:02:07.190 --> 01:02:08.782
What's wrong with you?

01:02:13.196 --> 01:02:15.630
Nothing.
What do you mean?

01:02:15.698 --> 01:02:18.132
I was just giving
you an answer.

01:02:18.201 --> 01:02:21.295
If they bring up the therapy,
it's not you.

01:02:21.370 --> 01:02:22.302
I'm going.

01:02:22.371 --> 01:02:23.702
I'll need another note card.

01:02:23.773 --> 01:02:25.502
Just forget it.
Forget it.

01:02:27.477 --> 01:02:29.911
...This press conference
will lay that to rest.

01:02:29.979 --> 01:02:31.640
Now, uh... Oh, O.K.,

01:02:31.714 --> 01:02:33.648
I want to give you all

01:02:33.716 --> 01:02:37.049
a crack at the new pride of
the Yankees... Steve Nebraska.

01:02:38.721 --> 01:02:40.154
Are you in therapy?

01:02:40.223 --> 01:02:42.589
Why you in therapy, Steve?

01:02:42.658 --> 01:02:44.592
Ohh! Time out!

01:02:44.660 --> 01:02:47.151
Let's all ask questions
one at a time.

01:02:47.230 --> 01:02:49.164
Then we'll move this along,

01:02:49.232 --> 01:02:52.167
and I can answer
your questions.

01:02:52.235 --> 01:02:53.964
Are you currently in therapy?

01:02:54.036 --> 01:02:55.469
Uh, nope.

01:02:55.538 --> 01:02:58.666
You've been seen coming in and out
of a doctor's office.

01:02:58.741 --> 01:03:03.144
That's because I'm taking
my friend to that office.

01:03:03.212 --> 01:03:04.907
Who, Steve?

01:03:04.981 --> 01:03:06.243
Al Percolo.

01:03:06.315 --> 01:03:07.247
Your manager?

01:03:07.316 --> 01:03:08.681
Yeah, that's right.

01:03:08.751 --> 01:03:09.683
What's wrong with him?

01:03:09.752 --> 01:03:12.687
Uh...nothing.
I'm not a doctor.

01:03:12.755 --> 01:03:13.847
Ha ha ha ha.

01:03:13.923 --> 01:03:15.584
Where were you born?

01:03:15.658 --> 01:03:17.853
I was born in the Mideast.

01:03:17.927 --> 01:03:19.258
In the Mideast?

01:03:19.328 --> 01:03:20.659
Midwest.

01:03:20.730 --> 01:03:23.756
West... Midwest! Ha.

01:03:23.833 --> 01:03:25.767
I spent time in the Mideast.

01:03:25.835 --> 01:03:27.427
How much time?

01:03:27.503 --> 01:03:28.834
I spent...

01:03:28.905 --> 01:03:31.373
six years in the Mideast,

01:03:31.440 --> 01:03:32.873
Wait, hang on minute.

01:03:32.942 --> 01:03:34.375
Are your parents American?

01:03:34.443 --> 01:03:35.876
So far as I know,

01:03:35.945 --> 01:03:37.810
How'd you get to the Mideast?

01:03:37.880 --> 01:03:39.142
On an airplane,

01:03:39.215 --> 01:03:40.443
I 'll call you back.

01:03:40.516 --> 01:03:42.143
That's Steve Nebraska for you,

01:03:42.218 --> 01:03:44.686
Very odd past,
Spent time in the Middle East,

01:03:44.754 --> 01:03:47.154
hiked around Switzerland for years,
father went to Harvard,

01:03:47.223 --> 01:03:48.485
It goes on and on,

01:03:48.558 --> 01:03:51.049
I got to tel I you something.
You did great.

01:03:51.127 --> 01:03:53.061
You know how hard it is

01:03:53.129 --> 01:03:55.393
to make guys laugh
at a press conference?

01:03:55.464 --> 01:03:56.897
What if they find out

01:03:56.966 --> 01:03:59.332
some of that stuff
I said isn't true?

01:03:59.402 --> 01:04:00.869
How will they find out?

01:04:00.937 --> 01:04:02.199
They're reporters.

01:04:02.271 --> 01:04:04.671
The Yankees keep going
like they're going,

01:04:04.740 --> 01:04:06.469
we'll see this kid soon,

01:04:06.542 --> 01:04:09.136
The Yankees could be
in the World Series,

01:04:09.212 --> 01:04:10.577
Oh, please.

01:04:10.646 --> 01:04:12.978
All New Yorkers are
crossing their fingers,

01:04:13.049 --> 01:04:17.486
We hope Steve Nebraska's
the Yankees' gain and Cairo's loss,

01:04:17.553 --> 01:04:18.986
And I'm hungry, too.

01:04:19.055 --> 01:04:22.081
How could you be hungry?
You ate 30 minutes ago.

01:04:22.158 --> 01:04:23.420
Well, let's eat again.

01:04:23.492 --> 01:04:26.188
No, let's not eat again.

01:04:26.295 --> 01:04:29.230
I got two words
of advice for you...

01:04:29.298 --> 01:04:31.232
Fernando Valenzuela.

01:04:31.300 --> 01:04:34.701
He started out a pitcher,
wound up a truck.

01:04:34.770 --> 01:04:36.032
Hello?

01:04:36.105 --> 01:04:38.471
Mr. Percolo,
it's, uh, Dr. Aaron.

01:04:38.541 --> 01:04:40.702
I just saw Steve on television.

01:04:40.776 --> 01:04:42.710
Fantastic, wasn't he?

01:04:42.778 --> 01:04:45.713
I need to see you
in my office right away.

01:04:45.781 --> 01:04:48.215
Meet me there in half an hour.

01:04:48.284 --> 01:04:50.718
No, that'll be tough.
We're going out.

01:04:50.786 --> 01:04:53.778
Steinbrenner's gal got us
tickets for Tony Bennett.

01:04:53.856 --> 01:04:54.788
Could this wait?

01:04:54.857 --> 01:04:56.791
It's important.
No, it can't wait.

01:04:56.859 --> 01:04:58.588
One half hour, please.

01:04:58.661 --> 01:05:00.561
All right, we'll be there.

01:05:00.630 --> 01:05:03.724
I just need to see you.

01:05:03.799 --> 01:05:05.733
Why's that?

01:05:05.801 --> 01:05:07.359
Hello?

01:05:09.939 --> 01:05:11.429
Dr. Aaron!

01:05:16.812 --> 01:05:18.040
Hi.

01:05:18.114 --> 01:05:21.709
Mr. Percolo, I can't be connected
with this any more.

01:05:21.784 --> 01:05:22.808
That's all.

01:05:22.885 --> 01:05:24.944
What brought this on?

01:05:25.021 --> 01:05:27.216
Middle East? America's Cup?
A Rhodes Scholar?

01:05:27.290 --> 01:05:28.587
Where's all that from?

01:05:28.658 --> 01:05:30.592
He was worried
he'd forget stuff.

01:05:30.660 --> 01:05:32.594
We went over a few things.

01:05:32.662 --> 01:05:35.096
This man is trying
to reconnect his life.

01:05:35.164 --> 01:05:36.426
Don't make up stuff.

01:05:36.499 --> 01:05:38.524
I was just trying to help.

01:05:38.601 --> 01:05:41.263
I think you two should
find another doctor.

01:05:41.337 --> 01:05:43.271
I'm sorry, I cannot help you.

01:05:43.339 --> 01:05:44.601
You're the only doctor...

01:05:44.674 --> 01:05:45.606
Oh, please.

01:05:45.675 --> 01:05:47.199
Don't take the letter back.

01:05:47.276 --> 01:05:50.712
All right! I don't want
you around him any more.

01:05:50.780 --> 01:05:54.216
Let him come to therapy
by himself.

01:05:54.283 --> 01:05:55.875
Oh, new rules.

01:05:59.188 --> 01:06:01.782
You were the one who said,
"Stay with him

01:06:01.857 --> 01:06:04.291
24 hours a day,
he might be dangerous."

01:06:04.360 --> 01:06:06.920
I changed my mind.
You might be dangerous.

01:06:06.996 --> 01:06:10.295
I'll accept that. But you won't
take the letter back, right?

01:06:10.366 --> 01:06:12.800
Oh, you know...
I don't want to hear

01:06:12.868 --> 01:06:15.268
anything more about the letter.
Goodbye.

01:06:15.338 --> 01:06:16.566
Good night.

01:06:23.879 --> 01:06:25.642
And now, ladies and gentlemen,

01:06:25.715 --> 01:06:28.081
please welcome
Mr. Tony Bennett!

01:06:28.150 --> 01:06:31.415
~ I mean I want to be around ~

01:06:31.487 --> 01:06:33.648
~To see how he does it ~

01:06:33.723 --> 01:06:36.157
~When he breaks your heart ~

01:06:36.225 --> 01:06:37.317
~To bits ~

01:06:38.761 --> 01:06:42.424
~ Let's see
if that puzzle fits ~

01:06:43.532 --> 01:06:45.625
~ So fine ~

01:06:46.702 --> 01:06:47.634
Wow.

01:06:49.171 --> 01:06:51.002
~That's when I'll discover ~

01:06:51.073 --> 01:06:53.064
~That revenge is sweet ~

01:06:54.343 --> 01:06:56.311
~ As I sit there applaudin' ~

01:06:56.379 --> 01:06:58.779
~ From a front row seat ~

01:06:58.848 --> 01:07:01.544
~When somebody
breaks your heart ~

01:07:01.617 --> 01:07:05.417
~Just like you broke mine ~

01:07:06.956 --> 01:07:10.551
~ Oh ~

01:07:10.626 --> 01:07:13.117
~Yeah ~~

01:07:15.064 --> 01:07:15.996
Whoo! Whoo!

01:07:16.065 --> 01:07:17.123
Whoo whoo!

01:07:19.368 --> 01:07:20.960
- Good seats, huh?
- Huh?

01:07:22.671 --> 01:07:24.605
You're beautiful.
Thank you so much.

01:07:24.673 --> 01:07:26.265
Ladies and gentlemen, we have

01:07:26.342 --> 01:07:28.105
a very special
guest here tonight

01:07:28.177 --> 01:07:29.610
I'd love to introduce.

01:07:29.678 --> 01:07:32.977
I'm a huge fan of
the New York Yankees.

01:07:33.049 --> 01:07:34.482
Yeah, I am, too.

01:07:36.052 --> 01:07:37.212
How much has he had?

01:07:37.286 --> 01:07:38.548
A little.

01:07:40.489 --> 01:07:42.923
They might even get
into the World Series.

01:07:42.992 --> 01:07:44.425
What do you think?

01:07:45.494 --> 01:07:46.961
Al...

01:07:47.029 --> 01:07:48.929
Tony knows?

01:07:50.699 --> 01:07:53.259
And right over here,
we have someone

01:07:53.335 --> 01:07:56.498
who may turn out to be
greater than Babe Ruth.

01:07:56.572 --> 01:07:59.666
One of the great
ballplayers of all time...

01:07:59.742 --> 01:08:00.902
Mr. Steve Nebraska!

01:08:03.012 --> 01:08:03.944
You.

01:08:04.013 --> 01:08:05.776
Al!

01:08:05.848 --> 01:08:07.110
Stand up.

01:08:07.183 --> 01:08:09.344
Come on! They love you.

01:08:10.519 --> 01:08:13.147
Come on, Steve, stand up
and take a bow.

01:08:13.222 --> 01:08:15.122
Steve Nebraska!

01:08:15.191 --> 01:08:17.658
[Woman]
Stand up! Stand up!

01:08:17.725 --> 01:08:18.658
Yeah, man!

01:08:18.727 --> 01:08:19.988
Hi.

01:08:21.764 --> 01:08:23.356
Thank you, Tony.

01:08:24.966 --> 01:08:25.899
Hi.

01:08:28.203 --> 01:08:29.636
Hi.

01:08:29.705 --> 01:08:30.966
They love you.

01:08:31.040 --> 01:08:32.667
That's Tony Bennett!

01:08:32.741 --> 01:08:33.729
Yes.

01:08:33.809 --> 01:08:35.367
Sit down.

01:08:35.444 --> 01:08:36.877
[Tony] Steve Nebraska.

01:08:39.415 --> 01:08:41.042
Now...
hit it, Ralph.

01:08:41.117 --> 01:08:43.711
~ I left ~

01:08:43.786 --> 01:08:46.755
~ My heart ~

01:08:46.822 --> 01:08:48.483
Oh, God, no.

01:08:48.557 --> 01:08:52.515
[Off Key] ~ In San Francisco ~

01:08:52.595 --> 01:08:55.428
Steve, that's his! Shh!
That's his closer!

01:08:55.497 --> 01:08:58.661
~ High on a hill ~

01:08:58.734 --> 01:09:00.224
Oh, no.

01:09:00.301 --> 01:09:02.361
It was your idea.

01:09:02.438 --> 01:09:04.406
Steve!
Come on, everybody!

01:09:04.473 --> 01:09:06.532
- No, don't do it.
- ~To be ~

01:09:06.609 --> 01:09:10.272
~Where little cable cars ~

01:09:10.345 --> 01:09:13.747
~ Climb halfway to the stars ~

01:09:13.816 --> 01:09:14.747
Come on!

01:09:14.817 --> 01:09:19.082
~Though morning fog ~

01:09:19.154 --> 01:09:24.091
~ May fill the air ~

01:09:24.160 --> 01:09:26.127
~ I don't care ~

01:09:26.194 --> 01:09:29.790
~ My love waits there ~

01:09:29.865 --> 01:09:30.957
[Giggling]

01:09:31.033 --> 01:09:34.127
~ In San Francisco... ~~

01:09:34.203 --> 01:09:36.136
Do you speak English?

01:09:36.205 --> 01:09:37.466
Thank God.

01:09:37.540 --> 01:09:39.006
You were great.

01:09:39.073 --> 01:09:40.506
I'm not kidding.

01:09:40.576 --> 01:09:42.042
You could sing professionally.

01:09:42.111 --> 01:09:43.372
You think so?

01:09:43.444 --> 01:09:46.073
I wouldn't ask Tony Bennett
for any help.

01:09:46.148 --> 01:09:47.581
He wasn’t angry, Al.

01:09:47.649 --> 01:09:50.517
Nah. He loved having
his entire act taken.

01:10:00.229 --> 01:10:02.663
Good night, Jennifer.
Thank George for the tickets.

01:10:02.731 --> 01:10:03.663
Al.

01:10:03.732 --> 01:10:04.664
Yeah?

01:10:04.733 --> 01:10:06.667
I'm going to stay with Jennifer

01:10:06.735 --> 01:10:08.168
for a little while.

01:10:08.237 --> 01:10:10.467
It's midnight, kid.
Think that’s a good idea?

01:10:10.539 --> 01:10:12.734
We're going out
for something to eat.

01:10:12.808 --> 01:10:15.242
Something to eat?
You just had dinner.

01:10:15.311 --> 01:10:18.007
Do you want to gain
a hundred pounds?

01:10:18.080 --> 01:10:19.342
We talked about this.

01:10:19.415 --> 01:10:21.906
I'll put in my mouth
what I want to.

01:10:21.984 --> 01:10:23.576
Fine...but we’re getting up

01:10:23.652 --> 01:10:25.586
early in the morning
to practice.

01:10:25.654 --> 01:10:28.122
I think you should get
a good night's sleep.

01:10:28.190 --> 01:10:29.623
It's O.K., Steve.

01:10:29.692 --> 01:10:32.126
We can do something
another time.

01:10:32.194 --> 01:10:33.627
Just...
Just a minute.

01:10:33.696 --> 01:10:35.129
I'll be right back.

01:10:36.966 --> 01:10:39.833
Listen, you got to stop
telling me what to do, O.K.?

01:10:39.902 --> 01:10:43.099
I'm gonna eat and sleep
when I want to,

01:10:43.172 --> 01:10:45.606
and I'm gonna practice
when I want to!

01:10:45.674 --> 01:10:49.041
'Cause I'm the Yankee!
Not you!

01:10:49.111 --> 01:10:51.045
You got that?

01:11:39.495 --> 01:11:40.427
Hi.

01:11:41.730 --> 01:11:45.166
Sorry, the laundry
room is in use now.

01:11:51.907 --> 01:11:52.839
Here.

01:11:52.908 --> 01:11:54.341
What is that?

01:11:54.410 --> 01:11:56.605
That's a chocolate
baseball bat.

01:11:56.679 --> 01:11:58.613
I got it for you.

01:11:58.681 --> 01:12:00.478
Did you drop it?

01:12:00.549 --> 01:12:02.483
I... I got
a little hungry.

01:12:02.551 --> 01:12:06.078
Well, I appreciate it.
I'll treasure it always.

01:12:08.924 --> 01:12:10.858
I'm sorry I yelled at you.

01:12:10.926 --> 01:12:13.861
I've been going through
a lot of stuff with the doctor,

01:12:13.929 --> 01:12:16.363
and it's bringing up
a lot of stuff,

01:12:16.432 --> 01:12:17.694
and I'm thinking about...

01:12:17.766 --> 01:12:18.698
um, the...

01:12:20.102 --> 01:12:23.162
I'm, uh, uh, ahem!
I gotta work it out.

01:12:23.238 --> 01:12:24.535
O.K.

01:12:24.606 --> 01:12:27.006
I appreciate the gift.

01:12:27.076 --> 01:12:28.008
Thank you.

01:12:28.077 --> 01:12:30.511
So did you have a good time?

01:12:30.579 --> 01:12:31.511
Yeah.

01:12:31.580 --> 01:12:33.172
Did you go eat again?

01:12:33.248 --> 01:12:36.051
Just the bat.
Don't leave that in the sun.

01:12:36.185 --> 01:12:37.709
O.K.

01:12:38.787 --> 01:12:41.051
So, uh...
what'd you guys do?

01:12:41.123 --> 01:12:42.715
Went back to her place.

01:12:42.791 --> 01:12:44.725
Oh.

01:12:44.793 --> 01:12:46.727
Did you, um...

01:12:48.564 --> 01:12:51.897
Well, sorry, that's
none of my business.

01:12:51.967 --> 01:12:53.366
Did I nail her?

01:12:53.435 --> 01:12:55.995
Well, now that you brought it up...
did you?

01:12:56.071 --> 01:12:57.561
No, I didn't.

01:12:57.639 --> 01:12:59.869
If you're gonna do that...
with anybody...

01:12:59.942 --> 01:13:02.172
you know to use
protection, don’t you?

01:13:02.244 --> 01:13:05.509
Oh, no. Now am I going
to get a lecture on this?

01:13:05.581 --> 01:13:07.515
I'm not lecturing.
I'm telling you.

01:13:07.583 --> 01:13:09.517
It's a dangerous
world out there.

01:13:09.585 --> 01:13:11.519
This is New York, not Mexico.

01:13:11.587 --> 01:13:12.849
I didn't do anything.

01:13:12.921 --> 01:13:14.855
I'm just saying "if,"
that's all.

01:13:14.923 --> 01:13:15.890
O.K. "If."

01:13:15.958 --> 01:13:17.016
[Bell Rings]

01:13:24.666 --> 01:13:25.598
Al.

01:13:25.667 --> 01:13:26.599
Hmm?

01:13:26.668 --> 01:13:28.101
You should separate those.

01:13:28.170 --> 01:13:30.764
You can't mix
the white one and dark ones.

01:13:30.839 --> 01:13:33.774
The dye from the dark ones
gets in the white ones.

01:13:33.842 --> 01:13:35.776
You're an expert on laundry?

01:13:35.844 --> 01:13:38.642
Well, actually,
I know a lot about laundry.

01:13:38.714 --> 01:13:42.115
I like doing laundry.
I find it very relaxing.

01:13:42.184 --> 01:13:43.116
Go figure.

01:13:46.021 --> 01:13:50.390
Go get some sleep. We're going
to practice at 8:30 a.m. Sharp.

01:13:52.127 --> 01:13:53.059
Um...

01:13:53.128 --> 01:13:55.756
Al, did you lie to me?

01:13:55.831 --> 01:13:57.560
What are you talking about?

01:13:57.633 --> 01:14:01.797
Well...you said that I wouldn't
have to pitch this year.

01:14:01.870 --> 01:14:03.360
I didn't say that.

01:14:03.439 --> 01:14:05.634
I said you wouldn't
have to pitch

01:14:05.707 --> 01:14:08.141
if the Yankees didn't
win the pennant.

01:14:08.210 --> 01:14:11.646
It's a shoe-in.
Doorman said so.

01:14:11.713 --> 01:14:12.737
The doorman?

01:14:12.815 --> 01:14:15.579
The doorman is a man
with an animal's brain.

01:14:15.651 --> 01:14:18.142
Just get
some sleep, O.K.?

01:14:18.220 --> 01:14:20.654
I'm still not ready
to pitch, Al.

01:14:20.722 --> 01:14:23.156
Why do you think
we need to practice?

01:14:23.225 --> 01:14:24.749
Who's gonna catch me?

01:14:24.827 --> 01:14:26.522
Al Percolo.

01:14:26.595 --> 01:14:30.429
You're gonna catch me?
I'm too fast for you. I'll hurt you.

01:14:30.499 --> 01:14:32.262
Just rest your little head

01:14:32.334 --> 01:14:34.768
and let me worry about this.

01:14:34.837 --> 01:14:36.805
I've taken your speed
into consideration.

01:14:36.972 --> 01:14:39.532
Come on, pitcher,
pitcher, pitcher!

01:14:39.608 --> 01:14:42.441
Fire it in, pitcher,
pitcher, pitcher!

01:14:42.511 --> 01:14:44.775
Al, I don't want
to pitch right now.

01:14:44.847 --> 01:14:48.283
O.K.? Come on. I'm fine.
I don't need to practice.

01:14:48.350 --> 01:14:50.978
It's me.
Let's go get some eggs.

01:14:51.053 --> 01:14:51.985
No eggs!

01:14:52.054 --> 01:14:53.487
We're here to pitch.

01:14:53.555 --> 01:14:56.285
Now, come on.
You felt like it earlier.

01:14:56.358 --> 01:14:58.792
Well, I don't feel like it now!

01:14:58.861 --> 01:15:00.795
